8 // ----
9 // This pass performs global value numbering to eliminate fully redundant ----
10 // instructions. It also performs simple dead load elimination. ----
11 // ----
12 // Note that this pass does the value numbering itself; it does not use the ----
13 // ValueNumbering analysis passes. ----
14 // ----
15 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----

137 struct llvm::GVNPass::Expression { ----
138 uint32_t opcode; ----
139 bool commutative = false; ----
140 // The type is not necessarily the result type of the expression, it may be ----
141 // any additional type needed to disambiguate the expression. ----
142 Type *type = nullptr; ----
143 SmallVector varargs; ----
144 ----
145 Expression(uint32_t o = ~2U) : opcode(o) {} 0
146 ----
147 bool operator==(const Expression &other) const { 0
148 if (opcode != other.opcode) 0
149 return false; 0
150 if (opcode == ~0U || opcode == ~1U) 0
151 return true; 0
152 if (type != other.type) 0
153 return false; 0
154 if (varargs != other.varargs) 0
155 return false; 0
156 return true; 0
157 } ----
158 ----
159 friend hash_code hash_value(const Expression &Value) { 0
160 return hash_combine( 0
161 Value.opcode, Value.type, 0
162 hash_combine_range(Value.varargs.begin(), Value.varargs.end())); 0
163 } ----
164 }; ----

186 /// Represents a particular available value that we know how to materialize. ----
187 /// Materialization of an AvailableValue never fails. An AvailableValue is ----
188 /// implicitly associated with a rematerialization point which is the ----
189 /// location of the instruction from which it was formed. ----
190 struct llvm::gvn::AvailableValue { ----
191 enum class ValType { ----
192 SimpleVal, // A simple offsetted value that is accessed. ----
193 LoadVal, // A value produced by a load. ----
194 MemIntrin, // A memory intrinsic which is loaded from. ----
195 UndefVal, // A UndefValue representing a value from dead block (which ----
196 // is not yet physically removed from the CFG). ----
197 SelectVal, // A pointer select which is loaded from and for which the load ----
198 // can be replace by a value select. ----
199 }; ----
200 ----
201 /// Val - The value that is live out of the block. ----
202 Value *Val; ----
203 /// Kind of the live-out value. ----
204 ValType Kind; ----
205 ----
206 /// Offset - The byte offset in Val that is interesting for the load query. ----
207 unsigned Offset = 0; ----
208 /// V1, V2 - The dominating non-clobbered values of SelectVal. ----
209 Value *V1 = nullptr, *V2 = nullptr; ----
210 ----
211 static AvailableValue get(Value *V, unsigned Offset = 0) { 0
212 AvailableValue Res; 0
213 Res.Val = V; 0
214 Res.Kind = ValType::SimpleVal; 0
215 Res.Offset = Offset; 0
216 return Res; 0
217 } ----
218 ----
219 static AvailableValue getMI(MemIntrinsic *MI, unsigned Offset = 0) { 0
220 AvailableValue Res; 0
221 Res.Val = MI; 0
222 Res.Kind = ValType::MemIntrin; 0
223 Res.Offset = Offset; 0
224 return Res; 0
225 } ----
226 ----
227 static AvailableValue getLoad(LoadInst *Load, unsigned Offset = 0) { 0
228 AvailableValue Res; 0
229 Res.Val = Load; 0
230 Res.Kind = ValType::LoadVal; 0
231 Res.Offset = Offset; 0
232 return Res; 0
233 } ----
234 ----
235 static AvailableValue getUndef() { 0
236 AvailableValue Res; 0
237 Res.Val = nullptr; 0
238 Res.Kind = ValType::UndefVal; 0
239 Res.Offset = 0; 0
240 return Res; 0
241 } ----
242 ----
243 static AvailableValue getSelect(SelectInst *Sel, Value *V1, Value *V2) { 0
244 AvailableValue Res; 0
245 Res.Val = Sel; 0
246 Res.Kind = ValType::SelectVal; 0
247 Res.Offset = 0; 0
248 Res.V1 = V1; 0
249 Res.V2 = V2; 0
250 return Res; 0
251 } ----
252 ----
253 bool isSimpleValue() const { return Kind == ValType::SimpleVal; } 0
254 bool isCoercedLoadValue() const { return Kind == ValType::LoadVal; } 0
255 bool isMemIntrinValue() const { return Kind == ValType::MemIntrin; } 0
256 bool isUndefValue() const { return Kind == ValType::UndefVal; } 0
257 bool isSelectValue() const { return Kind == ValType::SelectVal; } 0
258 ----
259 Value *getSimpleValue() const { 0
260 assert(isSimpleValue() && "Wrong accessor"); 0
261 return Val; 0
262 } ----
263 ----
264 LoadInst *getCoercedLoadValue() const { 0
265 assert(isCoercedLoadValue() && "Wrong accessor"); 0
266 return cast(Val); 0
267 } ----
268 ----
269 MemIntrinsic *getMemIntrinValue() const { 0
270 assert(isMemIntrinValue() && "Wrong accessor"); 0
271 return cast(Val); 0
272 } ----
273 ----
274 SelectInst *getSelectValue() const { 0
275 assert(isSelectValue() && "Wrong accessor"); 0
276 return cast(Val); 0
277 } ----

325 ----
326 GVNPass::Expression GVNPass::ValueTable::createExpr(Instruction *I) { 0
327 Expression e; 0
328 e.type = I->getType(); 0
329 e.opcode = I->getOpcode(); 0
330 if (const GCRelocateInst *GCR = dyn_cast(I)) { 0
331 // gc.relocate is 'special' call: its second and third operands are ----
332 // not real values, but indices into statepoint's argument list. ----
333 // Use the refered to values for purposes of identity. ----
334 e.varargs.push_back(lookupOrAdd(GCR->getOperand(0))); 0
335 e.varargs.push_back(lookupOrAdd(GCR->getBasePtr())); 0
336 e.varargs.push_back(lookupOrAdd(GCR->getDerivedPtr())); 0
337 } else { ----
338 for (Use &Op : I->operands()) 0
339 e.varargs.push_back(lookupOrAdd(Op)); 0
340 } ----
341 if (I->isCommutative()) { 0
342 // Ensure that commutative instructions that only differ by a permutation ----
343 // of their operands get the same value number by sorting the operand value ----
344 // numbers. Since commutative operands are the 1st two operands it is more ----
345 // efficient to sort by hand rather than using, say, std::sort. ----
346 assert(I->getNumOperands() >= 2 && "Unsupported commutative instruction!"); 0
347 if (e.varargs[0] > e.varargs[1]) 0
348 std::swap(e.varargs[0], e.varargs[1]); 0
349 e.commutative = true; 0
350 } ----
351 ----
352 if (auto *C = dyn_cast(I)) { 0
353 // Sort the operand value numbers so xx get the same value number. ----
354 CmpInst::Predicate Predicate = C->getPredicate(); 0
355 if (e.varargs[0] > e.varargs[1]) { 0
356 std::swap(e.varargs[0], e.varargs[1]); 0
357 Predicate = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Predicate); 0
358 } ----
359 e.opcode = (C->getOpcode() << 8) | Predicate; 0
360 e.commutative = true; 0
361 } else if (auto *E = dyn_cast(I)) { 0
362 e.varargs.append(E->idx_begin(), E->idx_end()); 0
363 } else if (auto *SVI = dyn_cast(I)) { 0
364 ArrayRef ShuffleMask = SVI->getShuffleMask(); 0
365 e.varargs.append(ShuffleMask.begin(), ShuffleMask.end()); 0
366 } ----
367 ----
368 return e; 0
369 } ----
370 ----
371 GVNPass::Expression GVNPass::ValueTable::createCmpExpr( 0
372 unsigned Opcode, CmpInst::Predicate Predicate, Value *LHS, Value *RHS) { ----
373 assert((Opcode == Instruction::ICmp || Opcode == Instruction::FCmp) && 0
374 "Not a comparison!"); ----
375 Expression e; 0
376 e.type = CmpInst::makeCmpResultType(LHS->getType()); 0
377 e.varargs.push_back(lookupOrAdd(LHS)); 0
378 e.varargs.push_back(lookupOrAdd(RHS)); 0
379 ----
380 // Sort the operand value numbers so xx get the same value number. ----
381 if (e.varargs[0] > e.varargs[1]) { 0
382 std::swap(e.varargs[0], e.varargs[1]); 0
383 Predicate = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Predicate); 0
384 } ----
385 e.opcode = (Opcode << 8) | Predicate; 0
386 e.commutative = true; 0
387 return e; 0
388 } ----

390 GVNPass::Expression ----
391 GVNPass::ValueTable::createExtractvalueExpr(ExtractValueInst *EI) { 0
392 assert(EI && "Not an ExtractValueInst?"); 0
393 Expression e; 0
394 e.type = EI->getType(); 0
395 e.opcode = 0; 0
396 ----
397 WithOverflowInst *WO = dyn_cast(EI->getAggregateOperand()); 0
398 if (WO != nullptr && EI->getNumIndices() == 1 && *EI->idx_begin() == 0) { 0
399 // EI is an extract from one of our with.overflow intrinsics. Synthesize ----
400 // a semantically equivalent expression instead of an extract value ----
401 // expression. ----
402 e.opcode = WO->getBinaryOp(); 0
403 e.varargs.push_back(lookupOrAdd(WO->getLHS())); 0
404 e.varargs.push_back(lookupOrAdd(WO->getRHS())); 0
405 return e; 0
406 } ----
407 ----
408 // Not a recognised intrinsic. Fall back to producing an extract value ----
409 // expression. ----
410 e.opcode = EI->getOpcode(); 0
411 for (Use &Op : EI->operands()) 0
412 e.varargs.push_back(lookupOrAdd(Op)); 0
413 ----
414 append_range(e.varargs, EI->indices()); 0
415 ----
416 return e; 0
417 } ----
418 ----
419 GVNPass::Expression GVNPass::ValueTable::createGEPExpr(GetElementPtrInst *GEP) { 0
420 Expression E; 0
421 Type *PtrTy = GEP->getType()->getScalarType(); 0
422 const DataLayout &DL = GEP->getModule()->getDataLayout(); 0
423 unsigned BitWidth = DL.getIndexTypeSizeInBits(PtrTy); 0
424 MapVector VariableOffsets; 0
425 APInt ConstantOffset(BitWidth, 0); 0
426 if (GEP->collectOffset(DL, BitWidth, VariableOffsets, ConstantOffset)) { 0
427 // Convert into offset representation, to recognize equivalent address ----
428 // calculations that use different type encoding. ----
429 LLVMContext &Context = GEP->getContext(); 0
430 E.opcode = GEP->getOpcode(); 0
431 E.type = nullptr; 0
432 E.varargs.push_back(lookupOrAdd(GEP->getPointerOperand())); 0
433 for (const auto &Pair : VariableOffsets) { 0
434 E.varargs.push_back(lookupOrAdd(Pair.first)); 0
435 E.varargs.push_back(lookupOrAdd(ConstantInt::get(Context, Pair.second))); 0
436 } ----
437 if (!ConstantOffset.isZero()) 0
438 E.varargs.push_back( 0
439 lookupOrAdd(ConstantInt::get(Context, ConstantOffset))); 0
440 } else { ----
441 // If converting to offset representation fails (for scalable vectors), ----
442 // fall back to type-based implementation: ----
443 E.opcode = GEP->getOpcode(); 0
444 E.type = GEP->getSourceElementType(); 0
445 for (Use &Op : GEP->operands()) 0
446 E.varargs.push_back(lookupOrAdd(Op)); 0
447 } ----
448 return E; 0
449 } 0

462 /// add - Insert a value into the table with a specified value number. ----
463 void GVNPass::ValueTable::add(Value *V, uint32_t num) { 0
464 valueNumbering.insert(std::make_pair(V, num)); 0
465 if (PHINode *PN = dyn_cast(V)) 0
466 NumberingPhi[num] = PN; 0
467 } 0
468 ----
469 uint32_t GVNPass::ValueTable::lookupOrAddCall(CallInst *C) { 0
470 // FIXME: Currently the calls which may access the thread id may ----
471 // be considered as not accessing the memory. But this is ----
472 // problematic for coroutines, since coroutines may resume in a ----
473 // different thread. So we disable the optimization here for the ----
474 // correctness. However, it may block many other correct ----
475 // optimizations. Revert this one when we detect the memory ----
476 // accessing kind more precisely. ----
477 if (C->getFunction()->isPresplitCoroutine()) { 0
478 valueNumbering[C] = nextValueNumber; 0
479 return nextValueNumber++; 0
480 } ----
481 ----
482 // Do not combine convergent calls since they implicitly depend on the set of ----
483 // threads that is currently executing, and they might be in different basic ----
484 // blocks. ----
485 if (C->isConvergent()) { 0
486 valueNumbering[C] = nextValueNumber; 0
487 return nextValueNumber++; 0
488 } ----
489 ----
490 if (AA->doesNotAccessMemory(C)) { 0
491 Expression exp = createExpr(C); 0
492 uint32_t e = assignExpNewValueNum(exp).first; 0
493 valueNumbering[C] = e; 0
494 return e; 0
495 } 0
496 ----
497 if (MD && AA->onlyReadsMemory(C)) { 0
498 Expression exp = createExpr(C); 0
499 auto ValNum = assignExpNewValueNum(exp); 0
500 if (ValNum.second) { 0
501 valueNumbering[C] = ValNum.first; 0
502 return ValNum.first; 0
503 } ----
504 ----
505 MemDepResult local_dep = MD->getDependency(C); 0
506 ----
507 if (!local_dep.isDef() && !local_dep.isNonLocal()) { 0
508 valueNumbering[C] = nextValueNumber; 0
509 return nextValueNumber++; 0
510 } ----
511 ----
512 if (local_dep.isDef()) { 0
513 // For masked load/store intrinsics, the local_dep may actually be ----
514 // a normal load or store instruction. ----
515 CallInst *local_cdep = dyn_cast(local_dep.getInst()); 0
516 ----
517 if (!local_cdep || local_cdep->arg_size() != C->arg_size()) { 0
518 valueNumbering[C] = nextValueNumber; 0
519 return nextValueNumber++; 0
520 } ----
521 ----
522 for (unsigned i = 0, e = C->arg_size(); i < e; ++i) { 0
523 uint32_t c_vn = lookupOrAdd(C->getArgOperand(i)); 0
524 uint32_t cd_vn = lookupOrAdd(local_cdep->getArgOperand(i)); 0
525 if (c_vn != cd_vn) { 0
526 valueNumbering[C] = nextValueNumber; 0
527 return nextValueNumber++; 0
528 } ----
529 } ----
530 ----
531 uint32_t v = lookupOrAdd(local_cdep); 0
532 valueNumbering[C] = v; 0
533 return v; 0
534 } ----
535 ----
536 // Non-local case. ----
537 const MemoryDependenceResults::NonLocalDepInfo &deps = ----
538 MD->getNonLocalCallDependency(C); 0
539 // FIXME: Move the checking logic to MemDep! ----
540 CallInst* cdep = nullptr; 0
541 ----
542 // Check to see if we have a single dominating call instruction that is ----
543 // identical to C. ----
544 for (const NonLocalDepEntry &I : deps) { 0
545 if (I.getResult().isNonLocal()) 0
546 continue; 0
547 ----
548 // We don't handle non-definitions. If we already have a call, reject ----
549 // instruction dependencies. ----
550 if (!I.getResult().isDef() || cdep != nullptr) { 0
551 cdep = nullptr; 0
552 break; 0
553 } ----
554 ----
555 CallInst *NonLocalDepCall = dyn_cast(I.getResult().getInst()); 0
556 // FIXME: All duplicated with non-local case. ----
557 if (NonLocalDepCall && DT->properlyDominates(I.getBB(), C->getParent())) { 0
558 cdep = NonLocalDepCall; 0
559 continue; 0
560 } ----
561 ----
562 cdep = nullptr; 0
563 break; 0
564 } ----
565 ----
566 if (!cdep) { 0
567 valueNumbering[C] = nextValueNumber; 0
568 return nextValueNumber++; 0
569 } ----
570 ----
571 if (cdep->arg_size() != C->arg_size()) { 0
572 valueNumbering[C] = nextValueNumber; 0
573 return nextValueNumber++; 0
574 } ----
575 for (unsigned i = 0, e = C->arg_size(); i < e; ++i) { 0
576 uint32_t c_vn = lookupOrAdd(C->getArgOperand(i)); 0
577 uint32_t cd_vn = lookupOrAdd(cdep->getArgOperand(i)); 0
578 if (c_vn != cd_vn) { 0
579 valueNumbering[C] = nextValueNumber; 0
580 return nextValueNumber++; 0
581 } ----
582 } ----
583 ----
584 uint32_t v = lookupOrAdd(cdep); 0
585 valueNumbering[C] = v; 0
586 return v; 0
587 } 0
588 ----
589 valueNumbering[C] = nextValueNumber; 0
590 return nextValueNumber++; 0
591 } ----
592 ----
593 /// Returns true if a value number exists for the specified value. ----
594 bool GVNPass::ValueTable::exists(Value *V) const { 0
595 return valueNumbering.count(V) != 0; 0
596 } ----
597 ----
598 /// lookup_or_add - Returns the value number for the specified value, assigning ----
599 /// it a new number if it did not have one before. ----
600 uint32_t GVNPass::ValueTable::lookupOrAdd(Value *V) { 0
601 DenseMap::iterator VI = valueNumbering.find(V); 0
602 if (VI != valueNumbering.end()) 0
603 return VI->second; 0
604 ----
605 auto *I = dyn_cast(V); 0
606 if (!I) { 0
607 valueNumbering[V] = nextValueNumber; 0
608 return nextValueNumber++; 0
609 } ----
610 ----
611 Expression exp; 0
612 switch (I->getOpcode()) { 0
613 case Instruction::Call: 0
614 return lookupOrAddCall(cast(I)); 0
615 case Instruction::FNeg: 0
616 case Instruction::Add: ----
617 case Instruction::FAdd: ----
618 case Instruction::Sub: ----
619 case Instruction::FSub: ----
620 case Instruction::Mul: ----
621 case Instruction::FMul: ----
622 case Instruction::UDiv: ----
623 case Instruction::SDiv: ----
624 case Instruction::FDiv: ----
625 case Instruction::URem: ----
626 case Instruction::SRem: ----
627 case Instruction::FRem: ----
628 case Instruction::Shl: ----
629 case Instruction::LShr: ----
630 case Instruction::AShr: ----
631 case Instruction::And: ----
632 case Instruction::Or: ----
633 case Instruction::Xor: ----
634 case Instruction::ICmp: ----
635 case Instruction::FCmp: ----
636 case Instruction::Trunc: ----
637 case Instruction::ZExt: ----
638 case Instruction::SExt: ----
639 case Instruction::FPToUI: ----
640 case Instruction::FPToSI: ----
641 case Instruction::UIToFP: ----
642 case Instruction::SIToFP: ----
643 case Instruction::FPTrunc: ----
644 case Instruction::FPExt: ----
645 case Instruction::PtrToInt: ----
646 case Instruction::IntToPtr: ----
647 case Instruction::AddrSpaceCast: ----
648 case Instruction::BitCast: ----
649 case Instruction::Select: ----
650 case Instruction::Freeze: ----
651 case Instruction::ExtractElement: ----
652 case Instruction::InsertElement: ----
653 case Instruction::ShuffleVector: ----
654 case Instruction::InsertValue: ----
655 exp = createExpr(I); 0
656 break; 0
657 case Instruction::GetElementPtr: 0
658 exp = createGEPExpr(cast(I)); 0
659 break; 0
660 case Instruction::ExtractValue: 0
661 exp = createExtractvalueExpr(cast(I)); 0
662 break; 0
663 case Instruction::PHI: 0
664 valueNumbering[V] = nextValueNumber; 0
665 NumberingPhi[nextValueNumber] = cast(V); 0
666 return nextValueNumber++; 0
667 default: 0
668 valueNumbering[V] = nextValueNumber; 0
669 return nextValueNumber++; 0
670 } ----
671 ----
672 uint32_t e = assignExpNewValueNum(exp).first; 0
673 valueNumbering[V] = e; 0
674 return e; 0
675 } 0

677 /// Returns the value number of the specified value. Fails if ----
678 /// the value has not yet been numbered. ----
679 uint32_t GVNPass::ValueTable::lookup(Value *V, bool Verify) const { 0
680 DenseMap::const_iterator VI = valueNumbering.find(V); 0
681 if (Verify) { 0
682 assert(VI != valueNumbering.end() && "Value not numbered?"); 0
683 return VI->second; 0
684 } ----
685 return (VI != valueNumbering.end()) ? VI->second : 0; 0
686 } ----

688 /// Returns the value number of the given comparison, ----
689 /// assigning it a new number if it did not have one before. Useful when ----
690 /// we deduced the result of a comparison, but don't immediately have an ----
691 /// instruction realizing that comparison to hand. ----
692 uint32_t GVNPass::ValueTable::lookupOrAddCmp(unsigned Opcode, 0
693 CmpInst::Predicate Predicate, ----
694 Value *LHS, Value *RHS) { ----
695 Expression exp = createCmpExpr(Opcode, Predicate, LHS, RHS); 0
696 return assignExpNewValueNum(exp).first; 0
697 } 0

752 PreservedAnalyses GVNPass::run(Function &F, FunctionAnalysisManager &AM) { 0
753 // FIXME: The order of evaluation of these 'getResult' calls is very ----
754 // significant! Re-ordering these variables will cause GVN when run alone to ----
755 // be less effective! We should fix memdep and basic-aa to not exhibit this ----
756 // behavior, but until then don't change the order here. ----
757 auto &AC = AM.getResult(F); 0
758 auto &DT = AM.getResult(F); 0
759 auto &TLI = AM.getResult(F); 0
760 auto &AA = AM.getResult(F); 0
761 auto *MemDep = ----
762 isMemDepEnabled() ? &AM.getResult(F) : nullptr; 0
763 auto *LI = AM.getCachedResult(F); 0
764 auto *MSSA = AM.getCachedResult(F); 0
765 auto &ORE = AM.getResult(F); 0
766 bool Changed = runImpl(F, AC, DT, TLI, AA, MemDep, LI, &ORE, 0
767 MSSA ? &MSSA->getMSSA() : nullptr); 0
768 if (!Changed) 0
769 return PreservedAnalyses::all(); 0
770 PreservedAnalyses PA; 0
771 PA.preserve(); 0
772 PA.preserve(); 0
773 if (MSSA) 0
774 PA.preserve(); 0
775 if (LI) 0
776 PA.preserve(); 0
777 return PA; 0
778 } 0

808 ----
809 enum class AvailabilityState : char { ----
810 /// We know the block *is not* fully available. This is a fixpoint. ----
811 Unavailable = 0, ----
812 /// We know the block *is* fully available. This is a fixpoint. ----
813 Available = 1, ----
814 /// We do not know whether the block is fully available or not, ----
815 /// but we are currently speculating that it will be. ----
816 /// If it would have turned out that the block was, in fact, not fully ----
817 /// available, this would have been cleaned up into an Unavailable. ----
818 SpeculativelyAvailable = 2, ----
819 }; ----
820 ----
821 /// Return true if we can prove that the value ----
822 /// we're analyzing is fully available in the specified block. As we go, keep ----
823 /// track of which blocks we know are fully alive in FullyAvailableBlocks. This ----
824 /// map is actually a tri-state map with the following values: ----
825 /// 0) we know the block *is not* fully available. ----
826 /// 1) we know the block *is* fully available. ----
827 /// 2) we do not know whether the block is fully available or not, but we are ----
828 /// currently speculating that it will be. ----
829 static bool IsValueFullyAvailableInBlock( 0
830 BasicBlock *BB, ----
831 DenseMap &FullyAvailableBlocks) { ----
832 SmallVector Worklist; 0
833 std::optional UnavailableBB; 0
834 ----
835 // The number of times we didn't find an entry for a block in a map and ----
836 // optimistically inserted an entry marking block as speculatively available. ----
837 unsigned NumNewNewSpeculativelyAvailableBBs = 0; 0
838 ----
839 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
840 SmallSet NewSpeculativelyAvailableBBs; 0
841 SmallVector AvailableBBs; 0
842 #endif ----
843 ----
844 Worklist.emplace_back(BB); 0
845 while (!Worklist.empty()) { 0
846 BasicBlock *CurrBB = Worklist.pop_back_val(); // LoadFO - depth-first! 0
847 // Optimistically assume that the block is Speculatively Available and check ----
848 // to see if we already know about this block in one lookup. ----
849 std::pair::iterator, bool> IV = ----
850 FullyAvailableBlocks.try_emplace( 0
851 CurrBB, AvailabilityState::SpeculativelyAvailable); 0
852 AvailabilityState &State = IV.first->second; 0
853 ----
854 // Did the entry already exist for this block? ----
855 if (!IV.second) { 0
856 if (State == AvailabilityState::Unavailable) { 0
857 UnavailableBB = CurrBB; 0
858 break; // Backpropagate unavailability info. 0
859 } ----
860 ----
861 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
862 AvailableBBs.emplace_back(CurrBB); 0
863 #endif ----
864 continue; // Don't recurse further, but continue processing worklist. 0
865 } ----
866 ----
867 // No entry found for block. ----
868 ++NumNewNewSpeculativelyAvailableBBs; 0
869 bool OutOfBudget = NumNewNewSpeculativelyAvailableBBs > MaxBBSpeculations; 0
870 ----
871 // If we have exhausted our budget, mark this block as unavailable. ----
872 // Also, if this block has no predecessors, the value isn't live-in here. ----
873 if (OutOfBudget || pred_empty(CurrBB)) { 0
874 MaxBBSpeculationCutoffReachedTimes += (int)OutOfBudget; 0
875 State = AvailabilityState::Unavailable; 0
876 UnavailableBB = CurrBB; 0
877 break; // Backpropagate unavailability info. 0
878 } ----
879 ----
880 // Tentatively consider this block as speculatively available. ----
881 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
882 NewSpeculativelyAvailableBBs.insert(CurrBB); 0
883 #endif ----
884 // And further recurse into block's predecessors, in depth-first order! ----
885 Worklist.append(pred_begin(CurrBB), pred_end(CurrBB)); 0
886 } ----
887 ----
888 #if LLVM_ENABLE_STATS ----
889 IsValueFullyAvailableInBlockNumSpeculationsMax.updateMax( 0
890 NumNewNewSpeculativelyAvailableBBs); ----
891 #endif ----
892 ----
893 // If the block isn't marked as fixpoint yet ----
894 // (the Unavailable and Available states are fixpoints) ----
895 auto MarkAsFixpointAndEnqueueSuccessors = ----
896 [&](BasicBlock *BB, AvailabilityState FixpointState) { 0
897 auto It = FullyAvailableBlocks.find(BB); 0
898 if (It == FullyAvailableBlocks.end()) 0
899 return; // Never queried this block, leave as-is. 0
900 switch (AvailabilityState &State = It->second) { 0
901 case AvailabilityState::Unavailable: 0
902 case AvailabilityState::Available: ----
903 return; // Don't backpropagate further, continue processing worklist. 0
904 case AvailabilityState::SpeculativelyAvailable: // Fix it! 0
905 State = FixpointState; 0
906 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
907 assert(NewSpeculativelyAvailableBBs.erase(BB) && 0
908 "Found a speculatively available successor leftover?"); ----
909 #endif ----
910 // Queue successors for further processing. ----
911 Worklist.append(succ_begin(BB), succ_end(BB)); 0
912 return; 0
913 } ----
914 }; 0
915 ----
916 if (UnavailableBB) { 0
917 // Okay, we have encountered an unavailable block. ----
918 // Mark speculatively available blocks reachable from UnavailableBB as ----
919 // unavailable as well. Paths are terminated when they reach blocks not in ----
920 // FullyAvailableBlocks or they are not marked as speculatively available. ----
921 Worklist.clear(); 0
922 Worklist.append(succ_begin(*UnavailableBB), succ_end(*UnavailableBB)); 0
923 while (!Worklist.empty()) 0
924 MarkAsFixpointAndEnqueueSuccessors(Worklist.pop_back_val(), 0
925 AvailabilityState::Unavailable); ----
926 } ----
927 ----
928 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
929 Worklist.clear(); 0
930 for (BasicBlock *AvailableBB : AvailableBBs) 0
931 Worklist.append(succ_begin(AvailableBB), succ_end(AvailableBB)); 0
932 while (!Worklist.empty()) 0
933 MarkAsFixpointAndEnqueueSuccessors(Worklist.pop_back_val(), 0
934 AvailabilityState::Available); ----
935 ----
936 assert(NewSpeculativelyAvailableBBs.empty() && 0
937 "Must have fixed all the new speculatively available blocks."); ----
938 #endif ----
939 ----
940 return !UnavailableBB; 0
941 } 0
942 ----
943 /// If the specified OldValue exists in ValuesPerBlock, replace its value with ----
944 /// NewValue. ----
945 static void replaceValuesPerBlockEntry( 0
946 SmallVectorImpl &ValuesPerBlock, Value *OldValue, ----
947 Value *NewValue) { ----
948 for (AvailableValueInBlock &V : ValuesPerBlock) { 0
949 if ((V.AV.isSimpleValue() && V.AV.getSimpleValue() == OldValue) || 0
950 (V.AV.isCoercedLoadValue() && V.AV.getCoercedLoadValue() == OldValue)) 0
951 V = AvailableValueInBlock::get(V.BB, NewValue); 0
952 } ----
953 } 0
954 ----
955 /// Given a set of loads specified by ValuesPerBlock, ----
956 /// construct SSA form, allowing us to eliminate Load. This returns the value ----
957 /// that should be used at Load's definition site. ----
958 static Value * ----
959 ConstructSSAForLoadSet(LoadInst *Load, 0
960 SmallVectorImpl &ValuesPerBlock, ----
961 GVNPass &gvn) { ----
962 // Check for the fully redundant, dominating load case. In this case, we can ----
963 // just use the dominating value directly. ----
964 if (ValuesPerBlock.size() == 1 && 0
965 gvn.getDominatorTree().properlyDominates(ValuesPerBlock[0].BB, 0
966 Load->getParent())) { 0
967 assert(!ValuesPerBlock[0].AV.isUndefValue() && 0
968 "Dead BB dominate this block"); ----
969 return ValuesPerBlock[0].MaterializeAdjustedValue(Load, gvn); 0
970 } ----
971 ----
972 // Otherwise, we have to construct SSA form. ----
973 SmallVector NewPHIs; 0
974 SSAUpdater SSAUpdate(&NewPHIs); 0
975 SSAUpdate.Initialize(Load->getType(), Load->getName()); 0
976 ----
977 for (const AvailableValueInBlock &AV : ValuesPerBlock) { 0
978 BasicBlock *BB = AV.BB; 0
979 ----
980 if (AV.AV.isUndefValue()) 0
981 continue; 0
982 ----
983 if (SSAUpdate.HasValueForBlock(BB)) 0
984 continue; 0
985 ----
986 // If the value is the load that we will be eliminating, and the block it's ----
987 // available in is the block that the load is in, then don't add it as ----
988 // SSAUpdater will resolve the value to the relevant phi which may let it ----
989 // avoid phi construction entirely if there's actually only one value. ----
990 if (BB == Load->getParent() && 0
991 ((AV.AV.isSimpleValue() && AV.AV.getSimpleValue() == Load) || 0
992 (AV.AV.isCoercedLoadValue() && AV.AV.getCoercedLoadValue() == Load))) 0
993 continue; 0
994 ----
995 SSAUpdate.AddAvailableValue(BB, AV.MaterializeAdjustedValue(Load, gvn)); 0
996 } ----
997 ----
998 // Perform PHI construction. ----
999 return SSAUpdate.GetValueInMiddleOfBlock(Load->getParent()); 0
1000 } 0
1001 ----
1002 Value *AvailableValue::MaterializeAdjustedValue(LoadInst *Load, 0
1003 Instruction *InsertPt, ----
1004 GVNPass &gvn) const { ----
1005 Value *Res; ----
1006 Type *LoadTy = Load->getType(); 0
1007 const DataLayout &DL = Load->getModule()->getDataLayout(); 0
1008 if (isSimpleValue()) { 0
1009 Res = getSimpleValue(); 0
1010 if (Res->getType() != LoadTy) { 0
1011 Res = getValueForLoad(Res, Offset, LoadTy, InsertPt, DL); 0
1012 ----
1013 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "GVN COERCED NONLOCAL VAL:\nOffset: " << Offset 0
1014 << " " << *getSimpleValue() << '\n' ----
1015 << *Res << '\n' ----
1016 << "\n\n\n"); ----
1017 } ----
1018 } else if (isCoercedLoadValue()) { 0
1019 LoadInst *CoercedLoad = getCoercedLoadValue(); 0
1020 if (CoercedLoad->getType() == LoadTy && Offset == 0) { 0
1021 Res = CoercedLoad; 0
1022 combineMetadataForCSE(CoercedLoad, Load, false); 0
1023 } else { ----
1024 Res = getValueForLoad(CoercedLoad, Offset, LoadTy, InsertPt, DL); 0
1025 // We are adding a new user for this load, for which the original ----
1026 // metadata may not hold. Additionally, the new load may have a different ----
1027 // size and type, so their metadata cannot be combined in any ----
1028 // straightforward way. ----
1029 // Drop all metadata that is not known to cause immediate UB on violation, ----
1030 // unless the load has !noundef, in which case all metadata violations ----
1031 // will be promoted to UB. ----
1032 // TODO: We can combine noalias/alias.scope metadata here, because it is ----
1033 // independent of the load type. ----
1034 if (!CoercedLoad->hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_noundef)) 0
1035 CoercedLoad->dropUnknownNonDebugMetadata( 0
1036 {LLVMContext::MD_dereferenceable, ----
1037 LLVMContext::MD_dereferenceable_or_null, ----
1038 LLVMContext::MD_invariant_load, LLVMContext::MD_invariant_group}); ----
1039 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "GVN COERCED NONLOCAL LOAD:\nOffset: " << Offset 0
1040 << " " << *getCoercedLoadValue() << '\n' ----
1041 << *Res << '\n' ----
1042 << "\n\n\n"); ----
1043 } ----
1044 } else if (isMemIntrinValue()) { 0
1045 Res = getMemInstValueForLoad(getMemIntrinValue(), Offset, LoadTy, 0
1046 InsertPt, DL); ----
1047 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "GVN COERCED NONLOCAL MEM INTRIN:\nOffset: " << Offset 0
1048 << " " << *getMemIntrinValue() << '\n' ----
1049 << *Res << '\n' ----
1050 << "\n\n\n"); ----
1051 } else if (isSelectValue()) { 0
1052 // Introduce a new value select for a load from an eligible pointer select. ----
1053 SelectInst *Sel = getSelectValue(); 0
1054 assert(V1 && V2 && "both value operands of the select must be present"); 0
1055 Res = SelectInst::Create(Sel->getCondition(), V1, V2, "", Sel); 0
1056 } else { ----
1057 llvm_unreachable("Should not materialize value from dead block"); 0
1058 } ----
1059 assert(Res && "failed to materialize?"); 0
1060 return Res; 0
1061 } ----

1063 static bool isLifetimeStart(const Instruction *Inst) { 0
1064 if (const IntrinsicInst* II = dyn_cast(Inst)) 0
1065 return II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::lifetime_start; 0
1066 return false; 0
1067 } ----
1068 ----
1069 /// Assuming To can be reached from both From and Between, does Between lie on ----
1070 /// every path from From to To? ----
1071 static bool liesBetween(const Instruction *From, Instruction *Between, 0
1072 const Instruction *To, DominatorTree *DT) { ----
1073 if (From->getParent() == Between->getParent()) 0
1074 return DT->dominates(From, Between); 0
1075 SmallSet Exclusion; 0
1076 Exclusion.insert(Between->getParent()); 0
1077 return !isPotentiallyReachable(From, To, &Exclusion, DT); 0
1078 } 0
1079 ----
1080 /// Try to locate the three instruction involved in a missed ----
1081 /// load-elimination case that is due to an intervening store. ----
1082 static void reportMayClobberedLoad(LoadInst *Load, MemDepResult DepInfo, 0
1083 DominatorTree *DT, ----
1084 OptimizationRemarkEmitter *ORE) { ----
1085 using namespace ore; ----
1086 ----
1087 Instruction *OtherAccess = nullptr; 0
1088 ----
1089 OptimizationRemarkMissed R(DEBUG_TYPE, "LoadClobbered", Load); 0
1090 R << "load of type " << NV("Type", Load->getType()) << " not eliminated" 0
1091 << setExtraArgs(); 0
1092 ----
1093 for (auto *U : Load->getPointerOperand()->users()) { 0
1094 if (U != Load && (isa(U) || isa(U))) { 0
1095 auto *I = cast(U); 0
1096 if (I->getFunction() == Load->getFunction() && DT->dominates(I, Load)) { 0
1097 // Use the most immediately dominating value ----
1098 if (OtherAccess) { 0
1099 if (DT->dominates(OtherAccess, I)) 0
1100 OtherAccess = I; 0
1101 else ----
1102 assert(U == OtherAccess || DT->dominates(I, OtherAccess)); 0
1103 } else ----
1104 OtherAccess = I; 0
1105 } ----
1106 } ----
1107 } ----
1108 ----
1109 if (!OtherAccess) { 0
1110 // There is no dominating use, check if we can find a closest non-dominating ----
1111 // use that lies between any other potentially available use and Load. ----
1112 for (auto *U : Load->getPointerOperand()->users()) { 0
1113 if (U != Load && (isa(U) || isa(U))) { 0
1114 auto *I = cast(U); 0
1115 if (I->getFunction() == Load->getFunction() && 0
1116 isPotentiallyReachable(I, Load, nullptr, DT)) { 0
1117 if (OtherAccess) { 0
1118 if (liesBetween(OtherAccess, I, Load, DT)) { 0
1119 OtherAccess = I; 0
1120 } else if (!liesBetween(I, OtherAccess, Load, DT)) { 0
1121 // These uses are both partially available at Load were it not for ----
1122 // the clobber, but neither lies strictly after the other. ----
1123 OtherAccess = nullptr; 0
1124 break; 0
1125 } // else: keep current OtherAccess since it lies between U and Load ----
1126 } else { ----
1127 OtherAccess = I; 0
1128 } ----
1129 } ----
1130 } ----
1131 } ----
1132 } ----
1133 ----
1134 if (OtherAccess) 0
1135 R << " in favor of " << NV("OtherAccess", OtherAccess); 0
1136 ----
1137 R << " because it is clobbered by " << NV("ClobberedBy", DepInfo.getInst()); 0
1138 ----
1139 ORE->emit(R); 0
1140 } 0
1141 ----
1142 // Find non-clobbered value for Loc memory location in extended basic block ----
1143 // (chain of basic blocks with single predecessors) starting From instruction. ----
1144 static Value *findDominatingValue(const MemoryLocation &Loc, Type *LoadTy, 0
1145 Instruction *From, AAResults *AA) { ----
1146 uint32_t NumVisitedInsts = 0; 0
1147 BasicBlock *FromBB = From->getParent(); 0
1148 BatchAAResults BatchAA(*AA); 0
1149 for (BasicBlock *BB = FromBB; BB; BB = BB->getSinglePredecessor()) 0
1150 for (auto I = BB == FromBB ? From->getReverseIterator() : BB->rbegin(), 0
1151 E = BB->rend(); 0
1152 I != E; ++I) { 0
1153 // Stop the search if limit is reached. ----
1154 if (++NumVisitedInsts > MaxNumVisitedInsts) 0
1155 return nullptr; 0
1156 Instruction *Inst = &*I; 0
1157 if (isModSet(BatchAA.getModRefInfo(Inst, Loc))) 0
1158 return nullptr; 0
1159 if (auto *LI = dyn_cast(Inst)) 0
1160 if (LI->getPointerOperand() == Loc.Ptr && LI->getType() == LoadTy) 0
1161 return LI; 0
1162 } ----
1163 return nullptr; 0
1164 } 0
1165 ----
1166 std::optional ----
1167 GVNPass::AnalyzeLoadAvailability(LoadInst *Load, MemDepResult DepInfo, 0
1168 Value *Address) { ----
1169 assert(Load->isUnordered() && "rules below are incorrect for ordered access"); 0
1170 assert(DepInfo.isLocal() && "expected a local dependence"); 0
1171 ----
1172 Instruction *DepInst = DepInfo.getInst(); 0
1173 ----
1174 const DataLayout &DL = Load->getModule()->getDataLayout(); 0
1175 if (DepInfo.isClobber()) { 0
1176 // If the dependence is to a store that writes to a superset of the bits ----
1177 // read by the load, we can extract the bits we need for the load from the ----
1178 // stored value. ----
1179 if (StoreInst *DepSI = dyn_cast(DepInst)) { 0
1180 // Can't forward from non-atomic to atomic without violating memory model. ----
1181 if (Address && Load->isAtomic() <= DepSI->isAtomic()) { 0
1182 int Offset = ----
1183 analyzeLoadFromClobberingStore(Load->getType(), Address, DepSI, DL); 0
1184 if (Offset != -1) 0
1185 return AvailableValue::get(DepSI->getValueOperand(), Offset); 0
1186 } ----
1187 } ----
1188 ----
1189 // Check to see if we have something like this: ----
1190 // load i32* P ----
1191 // load i8* (P+1) ----
1192 // if we have this, replace the later with an extraction from the former. ----
1193 if (LoadInst *DepLoad = dyn_cast(DepInst)) { 0
1194 // If this is a clobber and L is the first instruction in its block, then ----
1195 // we have the first instruction in the entry block. ----
1196 // Can't forward from non-atomic to atomic without violating memory model. ----
1197 if (DepLoad != Load && Address && 0
1198 Load->isAtomic() <= DepLoad->isAtomic()) { 0
1199 Type *LoadType = Load->getType(); 0
1200 int Offset = -1; 0
1201 ----
1202 // If MD reported clobber, check it was nested. ----
1203 if (DepInfo.isClobber() && 0
1204 canCoerceMustAliasedValueToLoad(DepLoad, LoadType, DL)) { 0
1205 const auto ClobberOff = MD->getClobberOffset(DepLoad); 0
1206 // GVN has no deal with a negative offset. ----
1207 Offset = (ClobberOff == std::nullopt || *ClobberOff < 0) 0
1208 ? -1 0
1209 : *ClobberOff; 0
1210 } ----
1211 if (Offset == -1) 0
1212 Offset = ----
1213 analyzeLoadFromClobberingLoad(LoadType, Address, DepLoad, DL); 0
1214 if (Offset != -1) 0
1215 return AvailableValue::getLoad(DepLoad, Offset); 0
1216 } ----
1217 } ----
1218 ----
1219 // If the clobbering value is a memset/memcpy/memmove, see if we can ----
1220 // forward a value on from it. ----
1221 if (MemIntrinsic *DepMI = dyn_cast(DepInst)) { 0
1222 if (Address && !Load->isAtomic()) { 0
1223 int Offset = analyzeLoadFromClobberingMemInst(Load->getType(), Address, 0
1224 DepMI, DL); ----
1225 if (Offset != -1) 0
1226 return AvailableValue::getMI(DepMI, Offset); 0
1227 } ----
1228 } ----
1229 ----
1230 // Nothing known about this clobber, have to be conservative ----
1231 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1232 // fast print dep, using operator<< on instruction is too slow. ----
1233 dbgs() << "GVN: load "; Load->printAsOperand(dbgs()); ----
1234 dbgs() << " is clobbered by " << *DepInst << '\n';); ----
1235 if (ORE->allowExtraAnalysis(DEBUG_TYPE)) 0
1236 reportMayClobberedLoad(Load, DepInfo, DT, ORE); 0
1237 ----
1238 return std::nullopt; 0
1239 } ----
1240 assert(DepInfo.isDef() && "follows from above"); 0
1241 ----
1242 // Loading the alloca -> undef. ----
1243 // Loading immediately after lifetime begin -> undef. ----
1244 if (isa(DepInst) || isLifetimeStart(DepInst)) 0
1245 return AvailableValue::get(UndefValue::get(Load->getType())); 0
1246 ----
1247 if (Constant *InitVal = 0
1248 getInitialValueOfAllocation(DepInst, TLI, Load->getType())) 0
1249 return AvailableValue::get(InitVal); 0
1250 ----
1251 if (StoreInst *S = dyn_cast(DepInst)) { 0
1252 // Reject loads and stores that are to the same address but are of ----
1253 // different types if we have to. If the stored value is convertable to ----
1254 // the loaded value, we can reuse it. ----
1255 if (!canCoerceMustAliasedValueToLoad(S->getValueOperand(), Load->getType(), 0
1256 DL)) ----
1257 return std::nullopt; 0
1258 ----
1259 // Can't forward from non-atomic to atomic without violating memory model. ----
1260 if (S->isAtomic() < Load->isAtomic()) 0
1261 return std::nullopt; 0
1262 ----
1263 return AvailableValue::get(S->getValueOperand()); 0
1264 } ----
1265 ----
1266 if (LoadInst *LD = dyn_cast(DepInst)) { 0
1267 // If the types mismatch and we can't handle it, reject reuse of the load. ----
1268 // If the stored value is larger or equal to the loaded value, we can reuse ----
1269 // it. ----
1270 if (!canCoerceMustAliasedValueToLoad(LD, Load->getType(), DL)) 0
1271 return std::nullopt; 0
1272 ----
1273 // Can't forward from non-atomic to atomic without violating memory model. ----
1274 if (LD->isAtomic() < Load->isAtomic()) 0
1275 return std::nullopt; 0
1276 ----
1277 return AvailableValue::getLoad(LD); 0
1278 } ----
1279 ----
1280 // Check if load with Addr dependent from select can be converted to select ----
1281 // between load values. There must be no instructions between the found ----
1282 // loads and DepInst that may clobber the loads. ----
1283 if (auto *Sel = dyn_cast(DepInst)) { 0
1284 assert(Sel->getType() == Load->getPointerOperandType()); 0
1285 auto Loc = MemoryLocation::get(Load); 0
1286 Value *V1 = ----
1287 findDominatingValue(Loc.getWithNewPtr(Sel->getTrueValue()), 0
1288 Load->getType(), DepInst, getAliasAnalysis()); ----
1289 if (!V1) 0
1290 return std::nullopt; 0
1291 Value *V2 = ----
1292 findDominatingValue(Loc.getWithNewPtr(Sel->getFalseValue()), 0
1293 Load->getType(), DepInst, getAliasAnalysis()); ----
1294 if (!V2) 0
1295 return std::nullopt; 0
1296 return AvailableValue::getSelect(Sel, V1, V2); 0
1297 } ----
1298 ----
1299 // Unknown def - must be conservative ----
1300 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1301 // fast print dep, using operator<< on instruction is too slow. ----
1302 dbgs() << "GVN: load "; Load->printAsOperand(dbgs()); ----
1303 dbgs() << " has unknown def " << *DepInst << '\n';); ----
1304 return std::nullopt; 0
1305 } ----
1306 ----
1307 void GVNPass::AnalyzeLoadAvailability(LoadInst *Load, LoadDepVect &Deps, 0
1308 AvailValInBlkVect &ValuesPerBlock, ----
1309 UnavailBlkVect &UnavailableBlocks) { ----
1310 // Filter out useless results (non-locals, etc). Keep track of the blocks ----
1311 // where we have a value available in repl, also keep track of whether we see ----
1312 // dependencies that produce an unknown value for the load (such as a call ----
1313 // that could potentially clobber the load). ----
1314 for (const auto &Dep : Deps) { 0
1315 BasicBlock *DepBB = Dep.getBB(); 0
1316 MemDepResult DepInfo = Dep.getResult(); 0
1317 ----
1318 if (DeadBlocks.count(DepBB)) { 0
1319 // Dead dependent mem-op disguise as a load evaluating the same value ----
1320 // as the load in question. ----
1321 ValuesPerBlock.push_back(AvailableValueInBlock::getUndef(DepBB)); 0
1322 continue; 0
1323 } ----
1324 ----
1325 if (!DepInfo.isLocal()) { 0
1326 UnavailableBlocks.push_back(DepBB); 0
1327 continue; 0
1328 } ----
1329 ----
1330 // The address being loaded in this non-local block may not be the same as ----
1331 // the pointer operand of the load if PHI translation occurs. Make sure ----
1332 // to consider the right address. ----
1333 if (auto AV = AnalyzeLoadAvailability(Load, DepInfo, Dep.getAddress())) { 0
1334 // subtlety: because we know this was a non-local dependency, we know ----
1335 // it's safe to materialize anywhere between the instruction within ----
1336 // DepInfo and the end of it's block. ----
1337 ValuesPerBlock.push_back( 0
1338 AvailableValueInBlock::get(DepBB, std::move(*AV))); 0
1339 } else { ----
1340 UnavailableBlocks.push_back(DepBB); 0
1341 } ----
1342 } ----
1343 ----
1344 assert(Deps.size() == ValuesPerBlock.size() + UnavailableBlocks.size() && 0
1345 "post condition violation"); ----
1346 } 0
1347 ----
1348 /// Given the following code, v1 is partially available on some edges, but not ----
1349 /// available on the edge from PredBB. This function tries to find if there is ----
1350 /// another identical load in the other successor of PredBB. ----
1351 /// ----
1352 /// v0 = load %addr ----
1353 /// br %LoadBB ----
1354 /// ----
1355 /// LoadBB: ----
1356 /// v1 = load %addr ----
1357 /// ... ----
1358 /// ----
1359 /// PredBB: ----
1360 /// ... ----
1361 /// br %cond, label %LoadBB, label %SuccBB ----
1362 /// ----
1363 /// SuccBB: ----
1364 /// v2 = load %addr ----
1365 /// ... ----
1366 /// ----
1367 LoadInst *GVNPass::findLoadToHoistIntoPred(BasicBlock *Pred, BasicBlock *LoadBB, 0
1368 LoadInst *Load) { ----
1369 // For simplicity we handle a Pred has 2 successors only. ----
1370 auto *Term = Pred->getTerminator(); 0
1371 if (Term->getNumSuccessors() != 2 || Term->isExceptionalTerminator()) 0
1372 return nullptr; 0
1373 auto *SuccBB = Term->getSuccessor(0); 0
1374 if (SuccBB == LoadBB) 0
1375 SuccBB = Term->getSuccessor(1); 0
1376 if (!SuccBB->getSinglePredecessor()) 0
1377 return nullptr; 0
1378 ----
1379 unsigned int NumInsts = MaxNumInsnsPerBlock; 0
1380 for (Instruction &Inst : *SuccBB) { 0
1381 if (Inst.isDebugOrPseudoInst()) 0
1382 continue; 0
1383 if (--NumInsts == 0) 0
1384 return nullptr; 0
1385 ----
1386 if (!Inst.isIdenticalTo(Load)) 0
1387 continue; 0
1388 ----
1389 MemDepResult Dep = MD->getDependency(&Inst); 0
1390 // If an identical load doesn't depends on any local instructions, it can ----
1391 // be safely moved to PredBB. ----
1392 // Also check for the implicit control flow instructions. See the comments ----
1393 // in PerformLoadPRE for details. ----
1394 if (Dep.isNonLocal() && !ICF->isDominatedByICFIFromSameBlock(&Inst)) 0
1395 return cast(&Inst); 0
1396 ----
1397 // Otherwise there is something in the same BB clobbers the memory, we can't ----
1398 // move this and later load to PredBB. ----
1399 return nullptr; 0
1400 } ----
1401 ----
1402 return nullptr; 0
1403 } ----
1404 ----
1405 void GVNPass::eliminatePartiallyRedundantLoad( 0
1406 LoadInst *Load, AvailValInBlkVect &ValuesPerBlock, ----
1407 MapVector &AvailableLoads, ----
1408 MapVector *CriticalEdgePredAndLoad) { ----
1409 for (const auto &AvailableLoad : AvailableLoads) { 0
1410 BasicBlock *UnavailableBlock = AvailableLoad.first; 0
1411 Value *LoadPtr = AvailableLoad.second; 0
1412 ----
1413 auto *NewLoad = ----
1414 new LoadInst(Load->getType(), LoadPtr, Load->getName() + ".pre", 0
1415 Load->isVolatile(), Load->getAlign(), Load->getOrdering(), 0
1416 Load->getSyncScopeID(), UnavailableBlock->getTerminator()); 0
1417 NewLoad->setDebugLoc(Load->getDebugLoc()); 0
1418 if (MSSAU) { 0
1419 auto *MSSA = MSSAU->getMemorySSA(); 0
1420 // Get the defining access of the original load or use the load if it is a ----
1421 // MemoryDef (e.g. because it is volatile). The inserted loads are ----
1422 // guaranteed to load from the same definition. ----
1423 auto *LoadAcc = MSSA->getMemoryAccess(Load); 0
1424 auto *DefiningAcc = ----
1425 isa(LoadAcc) ? LoadAcc : LoadAcc->getDefiningAccess(); 0
1426 auto *NewAccess = MSSAU->createMemoryAccessInBB( 0
1427 NewLoad, DefiningAcc, NewLoad->getParent(), 0
1428 MemorySSA::BeforeTerminator); ----
1429 if (auto *NewDef = dyn_cast(NewAccess)) 0
1430 MSSAU->insertDef(NewDef, /*RenameUses=*/true); 0
1431 else ----
1432 MSSAU->insertUse(cast(NewAccess), /*RenameUses=*/true); 0
1433 } ----
1434 ----
1435 // Transfer the old load's AA tags to the new load. ----
1436 AAMDNodes Tags = Load->getAAMetadata(); 0
1437 if (Tags) 0
1438 NewLoad->setAAMetadata(Tags); 0
1439 ----
1440 if (auto *MD = Load->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_invariant_load)) 0
1441 NewLoad->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_invariant_load, MD); 0
1442 if (auto *InvGroupMD = Load->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_invariant_group)) 0
1443 NewLoad->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_invariant_group, InvGroupMD); 0
1444 if (auto *RangeMD = Load->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range)) 0
1445 NewLoad->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range, RangeMD); 0
1446 if (auto *AccessMD = Load->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_access_group)) 0
1447 if (LI && 0
1448 LI->getLoopFor(Load->getParent()) == LI->getLoopFor(UnavailableBlock)) 0
1449 NewLoad->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_access_group, AccessMD); 0
1450 ----
1451 // We do not propagate the old load's debug location, because the new ----
1452 // load now lives in a different BB, and we want to avoid a jumpy line ----
1453 // table. ----
1454 // FIXME: How do we retain source locations without causing poor debugging ----
1455 // behavior? ----
1456 ----
1457 // Add the newly created load. ----
1458 ValuesPerBlock.push_back( 0
1459 AvailableValueInBlock::get(UnavailableBlock, NewLoad)); 0
1460 MD->invalidateCachedPointerInfo(LoadPtr); 0
1461 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "GVN INSERTED " << *NewLoad << '\n'); 0
1462 ----
1463 // For PredBB in CriticalEdgePredAndLoad we need to replace the uses of old ----
1464 // load instruction with the new created load instruction. ----
1465 if (CriticalEdgePredAndLoad) { 0
1466 auto I = CriticalEdgePredAndLoad->find(UnavailableBlock); 0
1467 if (I != CriticalEdgePredAndLoad->end()) { 0
1468 ++NumPRELoadMoved2CEPred; 0
1469 ICF->insertInstructionTo(NewLoad, UnavailableBlock); 0
1470 LoadInst *OldLoad = I->second; 0
1471 combineMetadataForCSE(NewLoad, OldLoad, false); 0
1472 OldLoad->replaceAllUsesWith(NewLoad); 0
1473 replaceValuesPerBlockEntry(ValuesPerBlock, OldLoad, NewLoad); 0
1474 if (uint32_t ValNo = VN.lookup(OldLoad, false)) 0
1475 removeFromLeaderTable(ValNo, OldLoad, OldLoad->getParent()); 0
1476 VN.erase(OldLoad); 0
1477 removeInstruction(OldLoad); 0
1478 } ----
1479 } ----
1480 } ----
1481 ----
1482 // Perform PHI construction. ----
1483 Value *V = ConstructSSAForLoadSet(Load, ValuesPerBlock, *this); 0
1484 // ConstructSSAForLoadSet is responsible for combining metadata. ----
1485 Load->replaceAllUsesWith(V); 0
1486 if (isa(V)) 0
1487 V->takeName(Load); 0
1488 if (Instruction *I = dyn_cast(V)) 0
1489 I->setDebugLoc(Load->getDebugLoc()); 0
1490 if (V->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy()) 0
1491 MD->invalidateCachedPointerInfo(V); 0
1492 markInstructionForDeletion(Load); 0
1493 ORE->emit([&]() { 0
1494 return OptimizationRemark(DEBUG_TYPE, "LoadPRE", Load) 0
1495 << "load eliminated by PRE"; 0
1496 }); ----
1497 } 0
1498 ----
1499 bool GVNPass::PerformLoadPRE(LoadInst *Load, AvailValInBlkVect &ValuesPerBlock, 0
1500 UnavailBlkVect &UnavailableBlocks) { ----
1501 // Okay, we have *some* definitions of the value. This means that the value ----
1502 // is available in some of our (transitive) predecessors. Lets think about ----
1503 // doing PRE of this load. This will involve inserting a new load into the ----
1504 // predecessor when it's not available. We could do this in general, but ----
1505 // prefer to not increase code size. As such, we only do this when we know ----
1506 // that we only have to insert *one* load (which means we're basically moving ----
1507 // the load, not inserting a new one). ----
1508 ----
1509 SmallPtrSet Blockers(UnavailableBlocks.begin(), ----
1510 UnavailableBlocks.end()); 0
1511 ----
1512 // Let's find the first basic block with more than one predecessor. Walk ----
1513 // backwards through predecessors if needed. ----
1514 BasicBlock *LoadBB = Load->getParent(); 0
1515 BasicBlock *TmpBB = LoadBB; 0
1516 ----
1517 // Check that there is no implicit control flow instructions above our load in ----
1518 // its block. If there is an instruction that doesn't always pass the ----
1519 // execution to the following instruction, then moving through it may become ----
1520 // invalid. For example: ----
1521 // ----
1522 // int arr[LEN]; ----
1523 // int index = ???; ----
1524 // ... ----
1525 // guard(0 <= index && index < LEN); ----
1526 // use(arr[index]); ----
1527 // ----
1528 // It is illegal to move the array access to any point above the guard, ----
1529 // because if the index is out of bounds we should deoptimize rather than ----
1530 // access the array. ----
1531 // Check that there is no guard in this block above our instruction. ----
1532 bool MustEnsureSafetyOfSpeculativeExecution = ----
1533 ICF->isDominatedByICFIFromSameBlock(Load); 0
1534 ----
1535 while (TmpBB->getSinglePredecessor()) { 0
1536 TmpBB = TmpBB->getSinglePredecessor(); 0
1537 if (TmpBB == LoadBB) // Infinite (unreachable) loop. 0
1538 return false; 0
1539 if (Blockers.count(TmpBB)) 0
1540 return false; 0
1541 ----
1542 // If any of these blocks has more than one successor (i.e. if the edge we ----
1543 // just traversed was critical), then there are other paths through this ----
1544 // block along which the load may not be anticipated. Hoisting the load ----
1545 // above this block would be adding the load to execution paths along ----
1546 // which it was not previously executed. ----
1547 if (TmpBB->getTerminator()->getNumSuccessors() != 1) 0
1548 return false; 0
1549 ----
1550 // Check that there is no implicit control flow in a block above. ----
1551 MustEnsureSafetyOfSpeculativeExecution = 0
1552 MustEnsureSafetyOfSpeculativeExecution || ICF->hasICF(TmpBB); 0
1553 } ----
1554 ----
1555 assert(TmpBB); 0
1556 LoadBB = TmpBB; 0
1557 ----
1558 // Check to see how many predecessors have the loaded value fully ----
1559 // available. ----
1560 MapVector PredLoads; 0
1561 DenseMap FullyAvailableBlocks; 0
1562 for (const AvailableValueInBlock &AV : ValuesPerBlock) 0
1563 FullyAvailableBlocks[AV.BB] = AvailabilityState::Available; 0
1564 for (BasicBlock *UnavailableBB : UnavailableBlocks) 0
1565 FullyAvailableBlocks[UnavailableBB] = AvailabilityState::Unavailable; 0
1566 ----
1567 // The edge from Pred to LoadBB is a critical edge will be splitted. ----
1568 SmallVector CriticalEdgePredSplit; 0
1569 // The edge from Pred to LoadBB is a critical edge, another successor of Pred ----
1570 // contains a load can be moved to Pred. This data structure maps the Pred to ----
1571 // the movable load. ----
1572 MapVector CriticalEdgePredAndLoad; 0
1573 for (BasicBlock *Pred : predecessors(LoadBB)) { 0
1574 // If any predecessor block is an EH pad that does not allow non-PHI ----
1575 // instructions before the terminator, we can't PRE the load. ----
1576 if (Pred->getTerminator()->isEHPad()) { 0
1577 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1578 dbgs() << "COULD NOT PRE LOAD BECAUSE OF AN EH PAD PREDECESSOR '" ----
1579 << Pred->getName() << "': " << *Load << '\n'); ----
1580 return false; 0
1581 } ----
1582 ----
1583 if (IsValueFullyAvailableInBlock(Pred, FullyAvailableBlocks)) { 0
1584 continue; 0
1585 } ----
1586 ----
1587 if (Pred->getTerminator()->getNumSuccessors() != 1) { 0
1588 if (isa(Pred->getTerminator())) { 0
1589 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1590 dbgs() << "COULD NOT PRE LOAD BECAUSE OF INDBR CRITICAL EDGE '" ----
1591 << Pred->getName() << "': " << *Load << '\n'); ----
1592 return false; 0
1593 } ----
1594 ----
1595 if (LoadBB->isEHPad()) { 0
1596 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1597 dbgs() << "COULD NOT PRE LOAD BECAUSE OF AN EH PAD CRITICAL EDGE '" ----
1598 << Pred->getName() << "': " << *Load << '\n'); ----
1599 return false; 0
1600 } ----
1601 ----
1602 // Do not split backedge as it will break the canonical loop form. ----
1603 if (!isLoadPRESplitBackedgeEnabled()) 0
1604 if (DT->dominates(LoadBB, Pred)) { 0
1605 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1606 dbgs() ----
1607 << "COULD NOT PRE LOAD BECAUSE OF A BACKEDGE CRITICAL EDGE '" ----
1608 << Pred->getName() << "': " << *Load << '\n'); ----
1609 return false; 0
1610 } ----
1611 ----
1612 if (LoadInst *LI = findLoadToHoistIntoPred(Pred, LoadBB, Load)) 0
1613 CriticalEdgePredAndLoad[Pred] = LI; 0
1614 else ----
1615 CriticalEdgePredSplit.push_back(Pred); 0
1616 } else { ----
1617 // Only add the predecessors that will not be split for now. ----
1618 PredLoads[Pred] = nullptr; 0
1619 } ----
1620 } ----
1621 ----
1622 // Decide whether PRE is profitable for this load. ----
1623 unsigned NumInsertPreds = PredLoads.size() + CriticalEdgePredSplit.size(); 0
1624 unsigned NumUnavailablePreds = NumInsertPreds + 0
1625 CriticalEdgePredAndLoad.size(); 0
1626 assert(NumUnavailablePreds != 0 && 0
1627 "Fully available value should already be eliminated!"); ----
1628 (void)NumUnavailablePreds; ----
1629 ----
1630 // If we need to insert new load in multiple predecessors, reject it. ----
1631 // FIXME: If we could restructure the CFG, we could make a common pred with ----
1632 // all the preds that don't have an available Load and insert a new load into ----
1633 // that one block. ----
1634 if (NumInsertPreds > 1) 0
1635 return false; 0
1636 ----
1637 // Now we know where we will insert load. We must ensure that it is safe ----
1638 // to speculatively execute the load at that points. ----
1639 if (MustEnsureSafetyOfSpeculativeExecution) { 0
1640 if (CriticalEdgePredSplit.size()) 0
1641 if (!isSafeToSpeculativelyExecute(Load, LoadBB->getFirstNonPHI(), AC, DT)) 0
1642 return false; 0
1643 for (auto &PL : PredLoads) 0
1644 if (!isSafeToSpeculativelyExecute(Load, PL.first->getTerminator(), AC, 0
1645 DT)) 0
1646 return false; 0
1647 for (auto &CEP : CriticalEdgePredAndLoad) 0
1648 if (!isSafeToSpeculativelyExecute(Load, CEP.first->getTerminator(), AC, 0
1649 DT)) 0
1650 return false; 0
1651 } ----
1652 ----
1653 // Split critical edges, and update the unavailable predecessors accordingly. ----
1654 for (BasicBlock *OrigPred : CriticalEdgePredSplit) { 0
1655 BasicBlock *NewPred = splitCriticalEdges(OrigPred, LoadBB); 0
1656 assert(!PredLoads.count(OrigPred) && "Split edges shouldn't be in map!"); 0
1657 PredLoads[NewPred] = nullptr; 0
1658 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Split critical edge " << OrigPred->getName() << "->" 0
1659 << LoadBB->getName() << '\n'); ----
1660 } ----
1661 ----
1662 for (auto &CEP : CriticalEdgePredAndLoad) 0
1663 PredLoads[CEP.first] = nullptr; 0
1664 ----
1665 // Check if the load can safely be moved to all the unavailable predecessors. ----
1666 bool CanDoPRE = true; 0
1667 const DataLayout &DL = Load->getModule()->getDataLayout(); 0
1668 SmallVector NewInsts; 0
1669 for (auto &PredLoad : PredLoads) { 0
1670 BasicBlock *UnavailablePred = PredLoad.first; 0
1671 ----
1672 // Do PHI translation to get its value in the predecessor if necessary. The ----
1673 // returned pointer (if non-null) is guaranteed to dominate UnavailablePred. ----
1674 // We do the translation for each edge we skipped by going from Load's block ----
1675 // to LoadBB, otherwise we might miss pieces needing translation. ----
1676 ----
1677 // If all preds have a single successor, then we know it is safe to insert ----
1678 // the load on the pred (?!?), so we can insert code to materialize the ----
1679 // pointer if it is not available. ----
1680 Value *LoadPtr = Load->getPointerOperand(); 0
1681 BasicBlock *Cur = Load->getParent(); 0
1682 while (Cur != LoadBB) { 0
1683 PHITransAddr Address(LoadPtr, DL, AC); 0
1684 LoadPtr = Address.translateWithInsertion(Cur, Cur->getSinglePredecessor(), 0
1685 *DT, NewInsts); 0
1686 if (!LoadPtr) { 0
1687 CanDoPRE = false; 0
1688 break; 0
1689 } ----
1690 Cur = Cur->getSinglePredecessor(); 0
1691 } 0
1692 ----
1693 if (LoadPtr) { 0
1694 PHITransAddr Address(LoadPtr, DL, AC); 0
1695 LoadPtr = Address.translateWithInsertion(LoadBB, UnavailablePred, *DT, 0
1696 NewInsts); ----
1697 } 0
1698 // If we couldn't find or insert a computation of this phi translated value, ----
1699 // we fail PRE. ----
1700 if (!LoadPtr) { 0
1701 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "COULDN'T INSERT PHI TRANSLATED VALUE OF: " 0
1702 << *Load->getPointerOperand() << "\n"); ----
1703 CanDoPRE = false; 0
1704 break; 0
1705 } ----
1706 ----
1707 PredLoad.second = LoadPtr; 0
1708 } ----
1709 ----
1710 if (!CanDoPRE) { 0
1711 while (!NewInsts.empty()) { 0
1712 // Erase instructions generated by the failed PHI translation before ----
1713 // trying to number them. PHI translation might insert instructions ----
1714 // in basic blocks other than the current one, and we delete them ----
1715 // directly, as markInstructionForDeletion only allows removing from the ----
1716 // current basic block. ----
1717 NewInsts.pop_back_val()->eraseFromParent(); 0
1718 } ----
1719 // HINT: Don't revert the edge-splitting as following transformation may ----
1720 // also need to split these critical edges. ----
1721 return !CriticalEdgePredSplit.empty(); 0
1722 } ----
1723 ----
1724 // Okay, we can eliminate this load by inserting a reload in the predecessor ----
1725 // and using PHI construction to get the value in the other predecessors, do ----
1726 // it. ----
1727 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "GVN REMOVING PRE LOAD: " << *Load << '\n'); 0
1728 LLVM_DEBUG(if (!NewInsts.empty()) dbgs() << "INSERTED " << NewInsts.size() 0
1729 << " INSTS: " << *NewInsts.back() ----
1730 << '\n'); ----
1731 ----
1732 // Assign value numbers to the new instructions. ----
1733 for (Instruction *I : NewInsts) { 0
1734 // Instructions that have been inserted in predecessor(s) to materialize ----
1735 // the load address do not retain their original debug locations. Doing ----
1736 // so could lead to confusing (but correct) source attributions. ----
1737 I->updateLocationAfterHoist(); 0
1738 ----
1739 // FIXME: We really _ought_ to insert these value numbers into their ----
1740 // parent's availability map. However, in doing so, we risk getting into ----
1741 // ordering issues. If a block hasn't been processed yet, we would be ----
1742 // marking a value as AVAIL-IN, which isn't what we intend. ----
1743 VN.lookupOrAdd(I); 0
1744 } ----
1745 ----
1746 eliminatePartiallyRedundantLoad(Load, ValuesPerBlock, PredLoads, 0
1747 &CriticalEdgePredAndLoad); ----
1748 ++NumPRELoad; 0
1749 return true; 0
1750 } 0
1751 ----
1752 bool GVNPass::performLoopLoadPRE(LoadInst *Load, 0
1753 AvailValInBlkVect &ValuesPerBlock, ----
1754 UnavailBlkVect &UnavailableBlocks) { ----
1755 if (!LI) 0
1756 return false; 0
1757 ----
1758 const Loop *L = LI->getLoopFor(Load->getParent()); 0
1759 // TODO: Generalize to other loop blocks that dominate the latch. ----
1760 if (!L || L->getHeader() != Load->getParent()) 0
1761 return false; 0
1762 ----
1763 BasicBlock *Preheader = L->getLoopPreheader(); 0
1764 BasicBlock *Latch = L->getLoopLatch(); 0
1765 if (!Preheader || !Latch) 0
1766 return false; 0
1767 ----
1768 Value *LoadPtr = Load->getPointerOperand(); 0
1769 // Must be available in preheader. ----
1770 if (!L->isLoopInvariant(LoadPtr)) 0
1771 return false; 0
1772 ----
1773 // We plan to hoist the load to preheader without introducing a new fault. ----
1774 // In order to do it, we need to prove that we cannot side-exit the loop ----
1775 // once loop header is first entered before execution of the load. ----
1776 if (ICF->isDominatedByICFIFromSameBlock(Load)) 0
1777 return false; 0
1778 ----
1779 BasicBlock *LoopBlock = nullptr; 0
1780 for (auto *Blocker : UnavailableBlocks) { 0
1781 // Blockers from outside the loop are handled in preheader. ----
1782 if (!L->contains(Blocker)) 0
1783 continue; 0
1784 ----
1785 // Only allow one loop block. Loop header is not less frequently executed ----
1786 // than each loop block, and likely it is much more frequently executed. But ----
1787 // in case of multiple loop blocks, we need extra information (such as block ----
1788 // frequency info) to understand whether it is profitable to PRE into ----
1789 // multiple loop blocks. ----
1790 if (LoopBlock) 0
1791 return false; 0
1792 ----
1793 // Do not sink into inner loops. This may be non-profitable. ----
1794 if (L != LI->getLoopFor(Blocker)) 0
1795 return false; 0
1796 ----
1797 // Blocks that dominate the latch execute on every single iteration, maybe ----
1798 // except the last one. So PREing into these blocks doesn't make much sense ----
1799 // in most cases. But the blocks that do not necessarily execute on each ----
1800 // iteration are sometimes much colder than the header, and this is when ----
1801 // PRE is potentially profitable. ----
1802 if (DT->dominates(Blocker, Latch)) 0
1803 return false; 0
1804 ----
1805 // Make sure that the terminator itself doesn't clobber. ----
1806 if (Blocker->getTerminator()->mayWriteToMemory()) 0
1807 return false; 0
1808 ----
1809 LoopBlock = Blocker; 0
1810 } ----
1811 ----
1812 if (!LoopBlock) 0
1813 return false; 0
1814 ----
1815 // Make sure the memory at this pointer cannot be freed, therefore we can ----
1816 // safely reload from it after clobber. ----
1817 if (LoadPtr->canBeFreed()) 0
1818 return false; 0
1819 ----
1820 // TODO: Support critical edge splitting if blocker has more than 1 successor. ----
1821 MapVector AvailableLoads; 0
1822 AvailableLoads[LoopBlock] = LoadPtr; 0
1823 AvailableLoads[Preheader] = LoadPtr; 0
1824 ----
1825 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "GVN REMOVING PRE LOOP LOAD: " << *Load << '\n'); 0
1826 eliminatePartiallyRedundantLoad(Load, ValuesPerBlock, AvailableLoads, 0
1827 /*CriticalEdgePredAndLoad*/ nullptr); ----
1828 ++NumPRELoopLoad; 0
1829 return true; 0
1830 } 0
1831 ----
1832 static void reportLoadElim(LoadInst *Load, Value *AvailableValue, 0
1833 OptimizationRemarkEmitter *ORE) { ----
1834 using namespace ore; ----
1835 ----
1836 ORE->emit([&]() { 0
1837 return OptimizationRemark(DEBUG_TYPE, "LoadElim", Load) 0
1838 << "load of type " << NV("Type", Load->getType()) << " eliminated" 0
1839 << setExtraArgs() << " in favor of " 0
1840 << NV("InfavorOfValue", AvailableValue); 0
1841 }); ----
1842 } 0
1843 ----
1844 /// Attempt to eliminate a load whose dependencies are ----
1845 /// non-local by performing PHI construction. ----
1846 bool GVNPass::processNonLocalLoad(LoadInst *Load) { 0
1847 // non-local speculations are not allowed under asan. ----
1848 if (Load->getParent()->getParent()->hasFnAttribute( 0
1849 Attribute::SanitizeAddress) || 0
1850 Load->getParent()->getParent()->hasFnAttribute( 0
1851 Attribute::SanitizeHWAddress)) ----
1852 return false; 0
1853 ----
1854 // Step 1: Find the non-local dependencies of the load. ----
1855 LoadDepVect Deps; 0
1856 MD->getNonLocalPointerDependency(Load, Deps); 0
1857 ----
1858 // If we had to process more than one hundred blocks to find the ----
1859 // dependencies, this load isn't worth worrying about. Optimizing ----
1860 // it will be too expensive. ----
1861 unsigned NumDeps = Deps.size(); 0
1862 if (NumDeps > MaxNumDeps) 0
1863 return false; 0
1864 ----
1865 // If we had a phi translation failure, we'll have a single entry which is a ----
1866 // clobber in the current block. Reject this early. ----
1867 if (NumDeps == 1 && 0
1868 !Deps[0].getResult().isDef() && !Deps[0].getResult().isClobber()) { 0
1869 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "GVN: non-local load "; Load->printAsOperand(dbgs()); 0
1870 dbgs() << " has unknown dependencies\n";); ----
1871 return false; 0
1872 } ----
1873 ----
1874 bool Changed = false; 0
1875 // If this load follows a GEP, see if we can PRE the indices before analyzing. ----
1876 if (GetElementPtrInst *GEP = 0
1877 dyn_cast(Load->getOperand(0))) { 0
1878 for (Use &U : GEP->indices()) 0
1879 if (Instruction *I = dyn_cast(U.get())) 0
1880 Changed |= performScalarPRE(I); 0
1881 } ----
1882 ----
1883 // Step 2: Analyze the availability of the load ----
1884 AvailValInBlkVect ValuesPerBlock; 0
1885 UnavailBlkVect UnavailableBlocks; 0
1886 AnalyzeLoadAvailability(Load, Deps, ValuesPerBlock, UnavailableBlocks); 0
1887 ----
1888 // If we have no predecessors that produce a known value for this load, exit ----
1889 // early. ----
1890 if (ValuesPerBlock.empty()) 0
1891 return Changed; 0
1892 ----
1893 // Step 3: Eliminate fully redundancy. ----
1894 // ----
1895 // If all of the instructions we depend on produce a known value for this ----
1896 // load, then it is fully redundant and we can use PHI insertion to compute ----
1897 // its value. Insert PHIs and remove the fully redundant value now. ----
1898 if (UnavailableBlocks.empty()) { 0
1899 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "GVN REMOVING NONLOCAL LOAD: " << *Load << '\n'); 0
1900 ----
1901 // Perform PHI construction. ----
1902 Value *V = ConstructSSAForLoadSet(Load, ValuesPerBlock, *this); 0
1903 // ConstructSSAForLoadSet is responsible for combining metadata. ----
1904 Load->replaceAllUsesWith(V); 0
1905 ----
1906 if (isa(V)) 0
1907 V->takeName(Load); 0
1908 if (Instruction *I = dyn_cast(V)) 0
1909 // If instruction I has debug info, then we should not update it. ----
1910 // Also, if I has a null DebugLoc, then it is still potentially incorrect ----
1911 // to propagate Load's DebugLoc because Load may not post-dominate I. ----
1912 if (Load->getDebugLoc() && Load->getParent() == I->getParent()) 0
1913 I->setDebugLoc(Load->getDebugLoc()); 0
1914 if (V->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy()) 0
1915 MD->invalidateCachedPointerInfo(V); 0
1916 markInstructionForDeletion(Load); 0
1917 ++NumGVNLoad; 0
1918 reportLoadElim(Load, V, ORE); 0
1919 return true; 0
1920 } ----
1921 ----
1922 // Step 4: Eliminate partial redundancy. ----
1923 if (!isPREEnabled() || !isLoadPREEnabled()) 0
1924 return Changed; 0
1925 if (!isLoadInLoopPREEnabled() && LI && LI->getLoopFor(Load->getParent())) 0
1926 return Changed; 0
1927 ----
1928 if (performLoopLoadPRE(Load, ValuesPerBlock, UnavailableBlocks) || 0
1929 PerformLoadPRE(Load, ValuesPerBlock, UnavailableBlocks)) 0
1930 return true; 0
1931 ----
1932 return Changed; 0
1933 } 0
1934 ----
1935 static bool impliesEquivalanceIfTrue(CmpInst* Cmp) { 0
1936 if (Cmp->getPredicate() == CmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_EQ) 0
1937 return true; 0
1938 ----
1939 // Floating point comparisons can be equal, but not equivalent. Cases: ----
1940 // NaNs for unordered operators ----
1941 // +0.0 vs 0.0 for all operators ----
1942 if (Cmp->getPredicate() == CmpInst::Predicate::FCMP_OEQ || 0
1943 (Cmp->getPredicate() == CmpInst::Predicate::FCMP_UEQ && 0
1944 Cmp->getFastMathFlags().noNaNs())) { 0
1945 Value *LHS = Cmp->getOperand(0); 0
1946 Value *RHS = Cmp->getOperand(1); 0
1947 // If we can prove either side non-zero, then equality must imply ----
1948 // equivalence. ----
1949 // FIXME: We should do this optimization if 'no signed zeros' is ----
1950 // applicable via an instruction-level fast-math-flag or some other ----
1951 // indicator that relaxed FP semantics are being used. ----
1952 if (isa(LHS) && !cast(LHS)->isZero()) 0
1953 return true; 0
1954 if (isa(RHS) && !cast(RHS)->isZero()) 0
1955 return true; 0
1956 // TODO: Handle vector floating point constants ----
1957 } ----
1958 return false; 0
1959 } ----
1960 ----
1961 static bool impliesEquivalanceIfFalse(CmpInst* Cmp) { 0
1962 if (Cmp->getPredicate() == CmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_NE) 0
1963 return true; 0
1964 ----
1965 // Floating point comparisons can be equal, but not equivelent. Cases: ----
1966 // NaNs for unordered operators ----
1967 // +0.0 vs 0.0 for all operators ----
1968 if ((Cmp->getPredicate() == CmpInst::Predicate::FCMP_ONE && 0
1969 Cmp->getFastMathFlags().noNaNs()) || 0
1970 Cmp->getPredicate() == CmpInst::Predicate::FCMP_UNE) { 0
1971 Value *LHS = Cmp->getOperand(0); 0
1972 Value *RHS = Cmp->getOperand(1); 0
1973 // If we can prove either side non-zero, then equality must imply ----
1974 // equivalence. ----
1975 // FIXME: We should do this optimization if 'no signed zeros' is ----
1976 // applicable via an instruction-level fast-math-flag or some other ----
1977 // indicator that relaxed FP semantics are being used. ----
1978 if (isa(LHS) && !cast(LHS)->isZero()) 0
1979 return true; 0
1980 if (isa(RHS) && !cast(RHS)->isZero()) 0
1981 return true; 0
1982 // TODO: Handle vector floating point constants ----
1983 } ----
1984 return false; 0
1985 } ----

1988 static bool hasUsersIn(Value *V, BasicBlock *BB) { 0
1989 return llvm::any_of(V->users(), [BB](User *U) { 0
1990 auto *I = dyn_cast(U); 0
1991 return I && I->getParent() == BB; 0
1992 }); 0
1993 } ----
1994 ----
1995 bool GVNPass::processAssumeIntrinsic(AssumeInst *IntrinsicI) { 0
1996 Value *V = IntrinsicI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1997 ----
1998 if (ConstantInt *Cond = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
1999 if (Cond->isZero()) { 0
2000 Type *Int8Ty = Type::getInt8Ty(V->getContext()); 0
2001 // Insert a new store to null instruction before the load to indicate that ----
2002 // this code is not reachable. FIXME: We could insert unreachable ----
2003 // instruction directly because we can modify the CFG. ----
2004 auto *NewS = new StoreInst(PoisonValue::get(Int8Ty), 0
2005 Constant::getNullValue(Int8Ty->getPointerTo()), 0
2006 IntrinsicI); 0
2007 if (MSSAU) { 0
2008 const MemoryUseOrDef *FirstNonDom = nullptr; 0
2009 const auto *AL = ----
2010 MSSAU->getMemorySSA()->getBlockAccesses(IntrinsicI->getParent()); 0
2011 ----
2012 // If there are accesses in the current basic block, find the first one ----
2013 // that does not come before NewS. The new memory access is inserted ----
2014 // after the found access or before the terminator if no such access is ----
2015 // found. ----
2016 if (AL) { 0
2017 for (const auto &Acc : *AL) { 0
2018 if (auto *Current = dyn_cast(&Acc)) 0
2019 if (!Current->getMemoryInst()->comesBefore(NewS)) { 0
2020 FirstNonDom = Current; 0
2021 break; 0
2022 } ----
2023 } ----
2024 } ----
2025 ----
2026 // This added store is to null, so it will never executed and we can ----
2027 // just use the LiveOnEntry def as defining access. ----
2028 auto *NewDef = ----
2029 FirstNonDom ? MSSAU->createMemoryAccessBefore( 0
2030 NewS, MSSAU->getMemorySSA()->getLiveOnEntryDef(), 0
2031 const_cast(FirstNonDom)) ----
2032 : MSSAU->createMemoryAccessInBB( 0
2033 NewS, MSSAU->getMemorySSA()->getLiveOnEntryDef(), 0
2034 NewS->getParent(), MemorySSA::BeforeTerminator); 0
2035 ----
2036 MSSAU->insertDef(cast(NewDef), /*RenameUses=*/false); 0
2037 } ----
2038 } ----
2039 if (isAssumeWithEmptyBundle(*IntrinsicI)) { 0
2040 markInstructionForDeletion(IntrinsicI); 0
2041 return true; 0
2042 } ----
2043 return false; 0
2044 } ----
2045 ----
2046 if (isa(V)) { 0
2047 // If it's not false, and constant, it must evaluate to true. This means our ----
2048 // assume is assume(true), and thus, pointless, and we don't want to do ----
2049 // anything more here. ----
2050 return false; 0
2051 } ----
2052 ----
2053 Constant *True = ConstantInt::getTrue(V->getContext()); 0
2054 bool Changed = false; 0
2055 ----
2056 for (BasicBlock *Successor : successors(IntrinsicI->getParent())) { 0
2057 BasicBlockEdge Edge(IntrinsicI->getParent(), Successor); 0
2058 ----
2059 // This property is only true in dominated successors, propagateEquality ----
2060 // will check dominance for us. ----
2061 Changed |= propagateEquality(V, True, Edge, false); 0
2062 } ----
2063 ----
2064 // We can replace assume value with true, which covers cases like this: ----
2065 // call void @llvm.assume(i1 %cmp) ----
2066 // br i1 %cmp, label %bb1, label %bb2 ; will change %cmp to true ----
2067 ReplaceOperandsWithMap[V] = True; 0
2068 ----
2069 // Similarly, after assume(!NotV) we know that NotV == false. ----
2070 Value *NotV; ----
2071 if (match(V, m_Not(m_Value(NotV)))) 0
2072 ReplaceOperandsWithMap[NotV] = ConstantInt::getFalse(V->getContext()); 0
2073 ----
2074 // If we find an equality fact, canonicalize all dominated uses in this block ----
2075 // to one of the two values. We heuristically choice the "oldest" of the ----
2076 // two where age is determined by value number. (Note that propagateEquality ----
2077 // above handles the cross block case.) ----
2078 // ----
2079 // Key case to cover are: ----
2080 // 1) ----
2081 // %cmp = fcmp oeq float 3.000000e+00, %0 ; const on lhs could happen ----
2082 // call void @llvm.assume(i1 %cmp) ----
2083 // ret float %0 ; will change it to ret float 3.000000e+00 ----
2084 // 2) ----
2085 // %load = load float, float* %addr ----
2086 // %cmp = fcmp oeq float %load, %0 ----
2087 // call void @llvm.assume(i1 %cmp) ----
2088 // ret float %load ; will change it to ret float %0 ----
2089 if (auto *CmpI = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
2090 if (impliesEquivalanceIfTrue(CmpI)) { 0
2091 Value *CmpLHS = CmpI->getOperand(0); 0
2092 Value *CmpRHS = CmpI->getOperand(1); 0
2093 // Heuristically pick the better replacement -- the choice of heuristic ----
2094 // isn't terribly important here, but the fact we canonicalize on some ----
2095 // replacement is for exposing other simplifications. ----
2096 // TODO: pull this out as a helper function and reuse w/existing ----
2097 // (slightly different) logic. ----
2098 if (isa(CmpLHS) && !isa(CmpRHS)) 0
2099 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS); 0
2100 if (!isa(CmpLHS) && isa(CmpRHS)) 0
2101 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS); 0
2102 if ((isa(CmpLHS) && isa(CmpRHS)) || 0
2103 (isa(CmpLHS) && isa(CmpRHS))) { 0
2104 // Move the 'oldest' value to the right-hand side, using the value ----
2105 // number as a proxy for age. ----
2106 uint32_t LVN = VN.lookupOrAdd(CmpLHS); 0
2107 uint32_t RVN = VN.lookupOrAdd(CmpRHS); 0
2108 if (LVN < RVN) 0
2109 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS); 0
2110 } ----
2111 ----
2112 // Handle degenerate case where we either haven't pruned a dead path or a ----
2113 // removed a trivial assume yet. ----
2114 if (isa(CmpLHS) && isa(CmpRHS)) 0
2115 return Changed; 0
2116 ----
2117 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Replacing dominated uses of " 0
2118 << *CmpLHS << " with " ----
2119 << *CmpRHS << " in block " ----
2120 << IntrinsicI->getParent()->getName() << "\n"); ----
2121 ----
2122 ----
2123 // Setup the replacement map - this handles uses within the same block ----
2124 if (hasUsersIn(CmpLHS, IntrinsicI->getParent())) 0
2125 ReplaceOperandsWithMap[CmpLHS] = CmpRHS; 0
2126 ----
2127 // NOTE: The non-block local cases are handled by the call to ----
2128 // propagateEquality above; this block is just about handling the block ----
2129 // local cases. TODO: There's a bunch of logic in propagateEqualiy which ----
2130 // isn't duplicated for the block local case, can we share it somehow? ----
2131 } ----
2132 } ----
2133 return Changed; 0
2134 } ----
2135 ----
2136 static void patchAndReplaceAllUsesWith(Instruction *I, Value *Repl) { 0
2137 patchReplacementInstruction(I, Repl); 0
2138 I->replaceAllUsesWith(Repl); 0
2139 } 0

2141 /// Attempt to eliminate a load, first by eliminating it ----
2142 /// locally, and then attempting non-local elimination if that fails. ----
2143 bool GVNPass::processLoad(LoadInst *L) { 0
2144 if (!MD) 0
2145 return false; 0
2146 ----
2147 // This code hasn't been audited for ordered or volatile memory access ----
2148 if (!L->isUnordered()) 0
2149 return false; 0
2150 ----
2151 if (L->use_empty()) { 0
2152 markInstructionForDeletion(L); 0
2153 return true; 0
2154 } ----
2155 ----
2156 // ... to a pointer that has been loaded from before... ----
2157 MemDepResult Dep = MD->getDependency(L); 0
2158 ----
2159 // If it is defined in another block, try harder. ----
2160 if (Dep.isNonLocal()) 0
2161 return processNonLocalLoad(L); 0
2162 ----
2163 // Only handle the local case below ----
2164 if (!Dep.isLocal()) { 0
2165 // This might be a NonFuncLocal or an Unknown ----
2166 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
2167 // fast print dep, using operator<< on instruction is too slow. ----
2168 dbgs() << "GVN: load "; L->printAsOperand(dbgs()); ----
2169 dbgs() << " has unknown dependence\n";); ----
2170 return false; 0
2171 } ----
2172 ----
2173 auto AV = AnalyzeLoadAvailability(L, Dep, L->getPointerOperand()); 0
2174 if (!AV) 0
2175 return false; 0
2176 ----
2177 Value *AvailableValue = AV->MaterializeAdjustedValue(L, L, *this); 0
2178 ----
2179 // MaterializeAdjustedValue is responsible for combining metadata. ----
2180 L->replaceAllUsesWith(AvailableValue); 0
2181 markInstructionForDeletion(L); 0
2182 if (MSSAU) 0
2183 MSSAU->removeMemoryAccess(L); 0
2184 ++NumGVNLoad; 0
2185 reportLoadElim(L, AvailableValue, ORE); 0
2186 // Tell MDA to reexamine the reused pointer since we might have more ----
2187 // information after forwarding it. ----
2188 if (MD && AvailableValue->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy()) 0
2189 MD->invalidateCachedPointerInfo(AvailableValue); 0
2190 return true; 0
2191 } ----

2194 /// second field showing whether it is a value number newly created. ----
2195 std::pair ----
2196 GVNPass::ValueTable::assignExpNewValueNum(Expression &Exp) { 0
2197 uint32_t &e = expressionNumbering[Exp]; 0
2198 bool CreateNewValNum = !e; 0
2199 if (CreateNewValNum) { 0
2200 Expressions.push_back(Exp); 0
2201 if (ExprIdx.size() < nextValueNumber + 1) 0
2202 ExprIdx.resize(nextValueNumber * 2); 0
2203 e = nextValueNumber; 0
2204 ExprIdx[nextValueNumber++] = nextExprNumber++; 0
2205 } ----
2206 return {e, CreateNewValNum}; 0
2207 } ----

2209 /// Return whether all the values related with the same \p num are ----
2210 /// defined in \p BB. ----
2211 bool GVNPass::ValueTable::areAllValsInBB(uint32_t Num, const BasicBlock *BB, 0
2212 GVNPass &Gvn) { ----
2213 LeaderTableEntry *Vals = &Gvn.LeaderTable[Num]; 0
2214 while (Vals && Vals->BB == BB) 0
2215 Vals = Vals->Next; 0
2216 return !Vals; 0
2217 } ----

2219 /// Wrap phiTranslateImpl to provide caching functionality. ----
2220 uint32_t GVNPass::ValueTable::phiTranslate(const BasicBlock *Pred, 0
2221 const BasicBlock *PhiBlock, ----
2222 uint32_t Num, GVNPass &Gvn) { ----
2223 auto FindRes = PhiTranslateTable.find({Num, Pred}); 0
2224 if (FindRes != PhiTranslateTable.end()) 0
2225 return FindRes->second; 0
2226 uint32_t NewNum = phiTranslateImpl(Pred, PhiBlock, Num, Gvn); 0
2227 PhiTranslateTable.insert({{Num, Pred}, NewNum}); 0
2228 return NewNum; 0
2229 } ----
