2231 // Return true if the value number \p Num and NewNum have equal value. ----
2232 // Return false if the result is unknown. ----
2233 bool GVNPass::ValueTable::areCallValsEqual(uint32_t Num, uint32_t NewNum, 0
2234 const BasicBlock *Pred, ----
2235 const BasicBlock *PhiBlock, ----
2236 GVNPass &Gvn) { ----
2237 CallInst *Call = nullptr; 0
2238 LeaderTableEntry *Vals = &Gvn.LeaderTable[Num]; 0
2239 while (Vals) { 0
2240 Call = dyn_cast(Vals->Val); 0
2241 if (Call && Call->getParent() == PhiBlock) 0
2242 break; 0
2243 Vals = Vals->Next; 0
2244 } ----
2245 ----
2246 if (AA->doesNotAccessMemory(Call)) 0
2247 return true; 0
2248 ----
2249 if (!MD || !AA->onlyReadsMemory(Call)) 0
2250 return false; 0
2251 ----
2252 MemDepResult local_dep = MD->getDependency(Call); 0
2253 if (!local_dep.isNonLocal()) 0
2254 return false; 0
2255 ----
2256 const MemoryDependenceResults::NonLocalDepInfo &deps = ----
2257 MD->getNonLocalCallDependency(Call); 0
2258 ----
2259 // Check to see if the Call has no function local clobber. ----
2260 for (const NonLocalDepEntry &D : deps) { 0
2261 if (D.getResult().isNonFuncLocal()) 0
2262 return true; 0
2263 } ----
2264 return false; 0
2265 } ----

2267 /// Translate value number \p Num using phis, so that it has the values of ----
2268 /// the phis in BB. ----
2269 uint32_t GVNPass::ValueTable::phiTranslateImpl(const BasicBlock *Pred, 0
2270 const BasicBlock *PhiBlock, ----
2271 uint32_t Num, GVNPass &Gvn) { ----
2272 if (PHINode *PN = NumberingPhi[Num]) { 0
2273 for (unsigned i = 0; i != PN->getNumIncomingValues(); ++i) { 0
2274 if (PN->getParent() == PhiBlock && PN->getIncomingBlock(i) == Pred) 0
2275 if (uint32_t TransVal = lookup(PN->getIncomingValue(i), false)) 0
2276 return TransVal; 0
2277 } ----
2278 return Num; 0
2279 } ----
2280 ----
2281 // If there is any value related with Num is defined in a BB other than ----
2282 // PhiBlock, it cannot depend on a phi in PhiBlock without going through ----
2283 // a backedge. We can do an early exit in that case to save compile time. ----
2284 if (!areAllValsInBB(Num, PhiBlock, Gvn)) 0
2285 return Num; 0
2286 ----
2287 if (Num >= ExprIdx.size() || ExprIdx[Num] == 0) 0
2288 return Num; 0
2289 Expression Exp = Expressions[ExprIdx[Num]]; 0
2290 ----
2291 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Exp.varargs.size(); i++) { 0
2292 // For InsertValue and ExtractValue, some varargs are index numbers ----
2293 // instead of value numbers. Those index numbers should not be ----
2294 // translated. ----
2295 if ((i > 1 && Exp.opcode == Instruction::InsertValue) || 0
2296 (i > 0 && Exp.opcode == Instruction::ExtractValue) || 0
2297 (i > 1 && Exp.opcode == Instruction::ShuffleVector)) 0
2298 continue; 0
2299 Exp.varargs[i] = phiTranslate(Pred, PhiBlock, Exp.varargs[i], Gvn); 0
2300 } ----
2301 ----
2302 if (Exp.commutative) { 0
2303 assert(Exp.varargs.size() >= 2 && "Unsupported commutative instruction!"); 0
2304 if (Exp.varargs[0] > Exp.varargs[1]) { 0
2305 std::swap(Exp.varargs[0], Exp.varargs[1]); 0
2306 uint32_t Opcode = Exp.opcode >> 8; 0
2307 if (Opcode == Instruction::ICmp || Opcode == Instruction::FCmp) 0
2308 Exp.opcode = (Opcode << 8) | 0
2309 CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate( 0
2310 static_cast(Exp.opcode & 255)); 0
2311 } ----
2312 } ----
2313 ----
2314 if (uint32_t NewNum = expressionNumbering[Exp]) { 0
2315 if (Exp.opcode == Instruction::Call && NewNum != Num) 0
2316 return areCallValsEqual(Num, NewNum, Pred, PhiBlock, Gvn) ? NewNum : Num; 0
2317 return NewNum; 0
2318 } ----
2319 return Num; 0
2320 } 0
2321 ----
2322 /// Erase stale entry from phiTranslate cache so phiTranslate can be computed ----
2323 /// again. ----
2324 void GVNPass::ValueTable::eraseTranslateCacheEntry( 0
2325 uint32_t Num, const BasicBlock &CurrBlock) { ----
2326 for (const BasicBlock *Pred : predecessors(&CurrBlock)) 0
2327 PhiTranslateTable.erase({Num, Pred}); 0
2328 } 0
2329 ----
2330 // In order to find a leader for a given value number at a ----
2331 // specific basic block, we first obtain the list of all Values for that number, ----
2332 // and then scan the list to find one whose block dominates the block in ----
2333 // question. This is fast because dominator tree queries consist of only ----
2334 // a few comparisons of DFS numbers. ----
2335 Value *GVNPass::findLeader(const BasicBlock *BB, uint32_t num) { 0
2336 LeaderTableEntry Vals = LeaderTable[num]; 0
2337 if (!Vals.Val) return nullptr; 0
2338 ----
2339 Value *Val = nullptr; 0
2340 if (DT->dominates(Vals.BB, BB)) { 0
2341 Val = Vals.Val; 0
2342 if (isa(Val)) return Val; 0
2343 } ----
2344 ----
2345 LeaderTableEntry* Next = Vals.Next; 0
2346 while (Next) { 0
2347 if (DT->dominates(Next->BB, BB)) { 0
2348 if (isa(Next->Val)) return Next->Val; 0
2349 if (!Val) Val = Next->Val; 0
2350 } ----
2351 ----
2352 Next = Next->Next; 0
2353 } ----
2354 ----
2355 return Val; 0
2356 } ----
2357 ----
2358 /// There is an edge from 'Src' to 'Dst'. Return ----
2359 /// true if every path from the entry block to 'Dst' passes via this edge. In ----
2360 /// particular 'Dst' must not be reachable via another edge from 'Src'. ----
2361 static bool isOnlyReachableViaThisEdge(const BasicBlockEdge &E, 0
2362 DominatorTree *DT) { ----
2363 // While in theory it is interesting to consider the case in which Dst has ----
2364 // more than one predecessor, because Dst might be part of a loop which is ----
2365 // only reachable from Src, in practice it is pointless since at the time ----
2366 // GVN runs all such loops have preheaders, which means that Dst will have ----
2367 // been changed to have only one predecessor, namely Src. ----
2368 const BasicBlock *Pred = E.getEnd()->getSinglePredecessor(); 0
2369 assert((!Pred || Pred == E.getStart()) && 0
2370 "No edge between these basic blocks!"); ----
2371 return Pred != nullptr; 0
2372 } ----
2373 ----
2374 void GVNPass::assignBlockRPONumber(Function &F) { 0
2375 BlockRPONumber.clear(); 0
2376 uint32_t NextBlockNumber = 1; 0
2377 ReversePostOrderTraversal RPOT(&F); 0
2378 for (BasicBlock *BB : RPOT) 0
2379 BlockRPONumber[BB] = NextBlockNumber++; 0
2380 InvalidBlockRPONumbers = false; 0
2381 } 0
2382 ----
2383 bool GVNPass::replaceOperandsForInBlockEquality(Instruction *Instr) const { 0
2384 bool Changed = false; 0
2385 for (unsigned OpNum = 0; OpNum < Instr->getNumOperands(); ++OpNum) { 0
2386 Value *Operand = Instr->getOperand(OpNum); 0
2387 auto it = ReplaceOperandsWithMap.find(Operand); 0
2388 if (it != ReplaceOperandsWithMap.end()) { 0
2389 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "GVN replacing: " << *Operand << " with " 0
2390 << *it->second << " in instruction " << *Instr << '\n'); ----
2391 Instr->setOperand(OpNum, it->second); 0
2392 Changed = true; 0
2393 } ----
2394 } ----
2395 return Changed; 0
2396 } ----
2397 ----
2398 /// The given values are known to be equal in every block ----
2399 /// dominated by 'Root'. Exploit this, for example by replacing 'LHS' with ----
2400 /// 'RHS' everywhere in the scope. Returns whether a change was made. ----
2401 /// If DominatesByEdge is false, then it means that we will propagate the RHS ----
2402 /// value starting from the end of Root.Start. ----
2403 bool GVNPass::propagateEquality(Value *LHS, Value *RHS, 0
2404 const BasicBlockEdge &Root, ----
2405 bool DominatesByEdge) { ----
2406 SmallVector, 4> Worklist; 0
2407 Worklist.push_back(std::make_pair(LHS, RHS)); 0
2408 bool Changed = false; 0
2409 // For speed, compute a conservative fast approximation to ----
2410 // DT->dominates(Root, Root.getEnd()); ----
2411 const bool RootDominatesEnd = isOnlyReachableViaThisEdge(Root, DT); 0
2412 ----
2413 while (!Worklist.empty()) { 0
2414 std::pair Item = Worklist.pop_back_val(); 0
2415 LHS = Item.first; RHS = Item.second; 0
2416 ----
2417 if (LHS == RHS) 0
2418 continue; 0
2419 assert(LHS->getType() == RHS->getType() && "Equality but unequal types!"); 0
2420 ----
2421 // Don't try to propagate equalities between constants. ----
2422 if (isa(LHS) && isa(RHS)) 0
2423 continue; 0
2424 ----
2425 // Prefer a constant on the right-hand side, or an Argument if no constants. ----
2426 if (isa(LHS) || (isa(LHS) && !isa(RHS))) 0
2427 std::swap(LHS, RHS); 0
2428 assert((isa(LHS) || isa(LHS)) && "Unexpected value!"); 0
2429 ----
2430 // If there is no obvious reason to prefer the left-hand side over the ----
2431 // right-hand side, ensure the longest lived term is on the right-hand side, ----
2432 // so the shortest lived term will be replaced by the longest lived. ----
2433 // This tends to expose more simplifications. ----
2434 uint32_t LVN = VN.lookupOrAdd(LHS); 0
2435 if ((isa(LHS) && isa(RHS)) || 0
2436 (isa(LHS) && isa(RHS))) { 0
2437 // Move the 'oldest' value to the right-hand side, using the value number ----
2438 // as a proxy for age. ----
2439 uint32_t RVN = VN.lookupOrAdd(RHS); 0
2440 if (LVN < RVN) { 0
2441 std::swap(LHS, RHS); 0
2442 LVN = RVN; 0
2443 } ----
2444 } ----
2445 ----
2446 // If value numbering later sees that an instruction in the scope is equal ----
2447 // to 'LHS' then ensure it will be turned into 'RHS'. In order to preserve ----
2448 // the invariant that instructions only occur in the leader table for their ----
2449 // own value number (this is used by removeFromLeaderTable), do not do this ----
2450 // if RHS is an instruction (if an instruction in the scope is morphed into ----
2451 // LHS then it will be turned into RHS by the next GVN iteration anyway, so ----
2452 // using the leader table is about compiling faster, not optimizing better). ----
2453 // The leader table only tracks basic blocks, not edges. Only add to if we ----
2454 // have the simple case where the edge dominates the end. ----
2455 if (RootDominatesEnd && !isa(RHS)) 0
2456 addToLeaderTable(LVN, RHS, Root.getEnd()); 0
2457 ----
2458 // Replace all occurrences of 'LHS' with 'RHS' everywhere in the scope. As ----
2459 // LHS always has at least one use that is not dominated by Root, this will ----
2460 // never do anything if LHS has only one use. ----
2461 if (!LHS->hasOneUse()) { 0
2462 unsigned NumReplacements = ----
2463 DominatesByEdge ----
2464 ? replaceDominatedUsesWith(LHS, RHS, *DT, Root) 0
2465 : replaceDominatedUsesWith(LHS, RHS, *DT, Root.getStart()); 0
2466 ----
2467 Changed |= NumReplacements > 0; 0
2468 NumGVNEqProp += NumReplacements; 0
2469 // Cached information for anything that uses LHS will be invalid. ----
2470 if (MD) 0
2471 MD->invalidateCachedPointerInfo(LHS); 0
2472 } ----
2473 ----
2474 // Now try to deduce additional equalities from this one. For example, if ----
2475 // the known equality was "(A != B)" == "false" then it follows that A and B ----
2476 // are equal in the scope. Only boolean equalities with an explicit true or ----
2477 // false RHS are currently supported. ----
2478 if (!RHS->getType()->isIntegerTy(1)) 0
2479 // Not a boolean equality - bail out. ----
2480 continue; 0
2481 ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(RHS); 0
2482 if (!CI) 0
2483 // RHS neither 'true' nor 'false' - bail out. ----
2484 continue; 0
2485 // Whether RHS equals 'true'. Otherwise it equals 'false'. ----
2486 bool isKnownTrue = CI->isMinusOne(); 0
2487 bool isKnownFalse = !isKnownTrue; 0
2488 ----
2489 // If "A && B" is known true then both A and B are known true. If "A || B" ----
2490 // is known false then both A and B are known false. ----
2491 Value *A, *B; ----
2492 if ((isKnownTrue && match(LHS, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(A), m_Value(B)))) || 0
2493 (isKnownFalse && match(LHS, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))))) { 0
2494 Worklist.push_back(std::make_pair(A, RHS)); 0
2495 Worklist.push_back(std::make_pair(B, RHS)); 0
2496 continue; 0
2497 } ----
2498 ----
2499 // If we are propagating an equality like "(A == B)" == "true" then also ----
2500 // propagate the equality A == B. When propagating a comparison such as ----
2501 // "(A >= B)" == "true", replace all instances of "A < B" with "false". ----
2502 if (CmpInst *Cmp = dyn_cast(LHS)) { 0
2503 Value *Op0 = Cmp->getOperand(0), *Op1 = Cmp->getOperand(1); 0
2504 ----
2505 // If "A == B" is known true, or "A != B" is known false, then replace ----
2506 // A with B everywhere in the scope. For floating point operations, we ----
2507 // have to be careful since equality does not always imply equivalance. ----
2508 if ((isKnownTrue && impliesEquivalanceIfTrue(Cmp)) || 0
2509 (isKnownFalse && impliesEquivalanceIfFalse(Cmp))) 0
2510 Worklist.push_back(std::make_pair(Op0, Op1)); 0
2511 ----
2512 // If "A >= B" is known true, replace "A < B" with false everywhere. ----
2513 CmpInst::Predicate NotPred = Cmp->getInversePredicate(); 0
2514 Constant *NotVal = ConstantInt::get(Cmp->getType(), isKnownFalse); 0
2515 // Since we don't have the instruction "A < B" immediately to hand, work ----
2516 // out the value number that it would have and use that to find an ----
2517 // appropriate instruction (if any). ----
2518 uint32_t NextNum = VN.getNextUnusedValueNumber(); 0
2519 uint32_t Num = VN.lookupOrAddCmp(Cmp->getOpcode(), NotPred, Op0, Op1); 0
2520 // If the number we were assigned was brand new then there is no point in ----
2521 // looking for an instruction realizing it: there cannot be one! ----
2522 if (Num < NextNum) { 0
2523 Value *NotCmp = findLeader(Root.getEnd(), Num); 0
2524 if (NotCmp && isa(NotCmp)) { 0
2525 unsigned NumReplacements = ----
2526 DominatesByEdge ----
2527 ? replaceDominatedUsesWith(NotCmp, NotVal, *DT, Root) 0
2528 : replaceDominatedUsesWith(NotCmp, NotVal, *DT, 0
2529 Root.getStart()); 0
2530 Changed |= NumReplacements > 0; 0
2531 NumGVNEqProp += NumReplacements; 0
2532 // Cached information for anything that uses NotCmp will be invalid. ----
2533 if (MD) 0
2534 MD->invalidateCachedPointerInfo(NotCmp); 0
2535 } ----
2536 } ----
2537 // Ensure that any instruction in scope that gets the "A < B" value number ----
2538 // is replaced with false. ----
2539 // The leader table only tracks basic blocks, not edges. Only add to if we ----
2540 // have the simple case where the edge dominates the end. ----
2541 if (RootDominatesEnd) 0
2542 addToLeaderTable(Num, NotVal, Root.getEnd()); 0
2543 ----
2544 continue; 0
2545 } 0
2546 } ----
2547 ----
2548 return Changed; 0
2549 } 0
2550 ----
2551 /// When calculating availability, handle an instruction ----
2552 /// by inserting it into the appropriate sets ----
2553 bool GVNPass::processInstruction(Instruction *I) { 0
2554 // Ignore dbg info intrinsics. ----
2555 if (isa(I)) 0
2556 return false; 0
2557 ----
2558 // If the instruction can be easily simplified then do so now in preference ----
2559 // to value numbering it. Value numbering often exposes redundancies, for ----
2560 // example if it determines that %y is equal to %x then the instruction ----
2561 // "%z = and i32 %x, %y" becomes "%z = and i32 %x, %x" which we now simplify. ----
2562 const DataLayout &DL = I->getModule()->getDataLayout(); 0
2563 if (Value *V = simplifyInstruction(I, {DL, TLI, DT, AC})) { 0
2564 bool Changed = false; 0
2565 if (!I->use_empty()) { 0
2566 // Simplification can cause a special instruction to become not special. ----
2567 // For example, devirtualization to a willreturn function. ----
2568 ICF->removeUsersOf(I); 0
2569 I->replaceAllUsesWith(V); 0
2570 Changed = true; 0
2571 } ----
2572 if (isInstructionTriviallyDead(I, TLI)) { 0
2573 markInstructionForDeletion(I); 0
2574 Changed = true; 0
2575 } ----
2576 if (Changed) { 0
2577 if (MD && V->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy()) 0
2578 MD->invalidateCachedPointerInfo(V); 0
2579 ++NumGVNSimpl; 0
2580 return true; 0
2581 } ----
2582 } ----
2583 ----
2584 if (auto *Assume = dyn_cast(I)) 0
2585 return processAssumeIntrinsic(Assume); 0
2586 ----
2587 if (LoadInst *Load = dyn_cast(I)) { 0
2588 if (processLoad(Load)) 0
2589 return true; 0
2590 ----
2591 unsigned Num = VN.lookupOrAdd(Load); 0
2592 addToLeaderTable(Num, Load, Load->getParent()); 0
2593 return false; 0
2594 } ----
2595 ----
2596 // For conditional branches, we can perform simple conditional propagation on ----
2597 // the condition value itself. ----
2598 if (BranchInst *BI = dyn_cast(I)) { 0
2599 if (!BI->isConditional()) 0
2600 return false; 0
2601 ----
2602 if (isa(BI->getCondition())) 0
2603 return processFoldableCondBr(BI); 0
2604 ----
2605 Value *BranchCond = BI->getCondition(); 0
2606 BasicBlock *TrueSucc = BI->getSuccessor(0); 0
2607 BasicBlock *FalseSucc = BI->getSuccessor(1); 0
2608 // Avoid multiple edges early. ----
2609 if (TrueSucc == FalseSucc) 0
2610 return false; 0
2611 ----
2612 BasicBlock *Parent = BI->getParent(); 0
2613 bool Changed = false; 0
2614 ----
2615 Value *TrueVal = ConstantInt::getTrue(TrueSucc->getContext()); 0
2616 BasicBlockEdge TrueE(Parent, TrueSucc); 0
2617 Changed |= propagateEquality(BranchCond, TrueVal, TrueE, true); 0
2618 ----
2619 Value *FalseVal = ConstantInt::getFalse(FalseSucc->getContext()); 0
2620 BasicBlockEdge FalseE(Parent, FalseSucc); 0
2621 Changed |= propagateEquality(BranchCond, FalseVal, FalseE, true); 0
2622 ----
2623 return Changed; 0
2624 } ----
2625 ----
2626 // For switches, propagate the case values into the case destinations. ----
2627 if (SwitchInst *SI = dyn_cast(I)) { 0
2628 Value *SwitchCond = SI->getCondition(); 0
2629 BasicBlock *Parent = SI->getParent(); 0
2630 bool Changed = false; 0
2631 ----
2632 // Remember how many outgoing edges there are to every successor. ----
2633 SmallDenseMap SwitchEdges; 0
2634 for (unsigned i = 0, n = SI->getNumSuccessors(); i != n; ++i) 0
2635 ++SwitchEdges[SI->getSuccessor(i)]; 0
2636 ----
2637 for (SwitchInst::CaseIt i = SI->case_begin(), e = SI->case_end(); 0
2638 i != e; ++i) { 0
2639 BasicBlock *Dst = i->getCaseSuccessor(); 0
2640 // If there is only a single edge, propagate the case value into it. ----
2641 if (SwitchEdges.lookup(Dst) == 1) { 0
2642 BasicBlockEdge E(Parent, Dst); 0
2643 Changed |= propagateEquality(SwitchCond, i->getCaseValue(), E, true); 0
2644 } ----
2645 } ----
2646 return Changed; 0
2647 } 0
2648 ----
2649 // Instructions with void type don't return a value, so there's ----
2650 // no point in trying to find redundancies in them. ----
2651 if (I->getType()->isVoidTy()) 0
2652 return false; 0
2653 ----
2654 uint32_t NextNum = VN.getNextUnusedValueNumber(); 0
2655 unsigned Num = VN.lookupOrAdd(I); 0
2656 ----
2657 // Allocations are always uniquely numbered, so we can save time and memory ----
2658 // by fast failing them. ----
2659 if (isa(I) || I->isTerminator() || isa(I)) { 0
2660 addToLeaderTable(Num, I, I->getParent()); 0
2661 return false; 0
2662 } ----
2663 ----
2664 // If the number we were assigned was a brand new VN, then we don't ----
2665 // need to do a lookup to see if the number already exists ----
2666 // somewhere in the domtree: it can't! ----
2667 if (Num >= NextNum) { 0
2668 addToLeaderTable(Num, I, I->getParent()); 0
2669 return false; 0
2670 } ----
2671 ----
2672 // Perform fast-path value-number based elimination of values inherited from ----
2673 // dominators. ----
2674 Value *Repl = findLeader(I->getParent(), Num); 0
2675 if (!Repl) { 0
2676 // Failure, just remember this instance for future use. ----
2677 addToLeaderTable(Num, I, I->getParent()); 0
2678 return false; 0
2679 } ----
2680 ----
2681 if (Repl == I) { 0
2682 // If I was the result of a shortcut PRE, it might already be in the table ----
2683 // and the best replacement for itself. Nothing to do. ----
2684 return false; 0
2685 } ----
2686 ----
2687 // Remove it! ----
2688 patchAndReplaceAllUsesWith(I, Repl); 0
2689 if (MD && Repl->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy()) 0
2690 MD->invalidateCachedPointerInfo(Repl); 0
2691 markInstructionForDeletion(I); 0
2692 return true; 0
2693 } ----
2694 ----
2695 /// runOnFunction - This is the main transformation entry point for a function. ----
2696 bool GVNPass::runImpl(Function &F, AssumptionCache &RunAC, DominatorTree &RunDT, 0
2697 const TargetLibraryInfo &RunTLI, AAResults &RunAA, ----
2698 MemoryDependenceResults *RunMD, LoopInfo *LI, ----
2699 OptimizationRemarkEmitter *RunORE, MemorySSA *MSSA) { ----
2700 AC = &RunAC; 0
2701 DT = &RunDT; 0
2702 VN.setDomTree(DT); 0
2703 TLI = &RunTLI; 0
2704 VN.setAliasAnalysis(&RunAA); 0
2705 MD = RunMD; 0
2706 ImplicitControlFlowTracking ImplicitCFT; 0
2707 ICF = &ImplicitCFT; 0
2708 this->LI = LI; 0
2709 VN.setMemDep(MD); 0
2710 ORE = RunORE; 0
2711 InvalidBlockRPONumbers = true; 0
2712 MemorySSAUpdater Updater(MSSA); 0
2713 MSSAU = MSSA ? &Updater : nullptr; 0
2714 ----
2715 bool Changed = false; 0
2716 bool ShouldContinue = true; 0
2717 ----
2718 DomTreeUpdater DTU(DT, DomTreeUpdater::UpdateStrategy::Eager); 0
2719 // Merge unconditional branches, allowing PRE to catch more ----
2720 // optimization opportunities. ----
2721 for (BasicBlock &BB : llvm::make_early_inc_range(F)) { 0
2722 bool removedBlock = MergeBlockIntoPredecessor(&BB, &DTU, LI, MSSAU, MD); 0
2723 if (removedBlock) 0
2724 ++NumGVNBlocks; 0
2725 ----
2726 Changed |= removedBlock; 0
2727 } ----
2728 ----
2729 unsigned Iteration = 0; 0
2730 while (ShouldContinue) { 0
2731 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "GVN iteration: " << Iteration << "\n"); 0
2732 (void) Iteration; ----
2733 ShouldContinue = iterateOnFunction(F); 0
2734 Changed |= ShouldContinue; 0
2735 ++Iteration; 0
2736 } ----
2737 ----
2738 if (isPREEnabled()) { 0
2739 // Fabricate val-num for dead-code in order to suppress assertion in ----
2740 // performPRE(). ----
2741 assignValNumForDeadCode(); 0
2742 bool PREChanged = true; 0
2743 while (PREChanged) { 0
2744 PREChanged = performPRE(F); 0
2745 Changed |= PREChanged; 0
2746 } ----
2747 } ----
2748 ----
2749 // FIXME: Should perform GVN again after PRE does something. PRE can move ----
2750 // computations into blocks where they become fully redundant. Note that ----
2751 // we can't do this until PRE's critical edge splitting updates memdep. ----
2752 // Actually, when this happens, we should just fully integrate PRE into GVN. ----
2753 ----
2754 cleanupGlobalSets(); 0
2755 // Do not cleanup DeadBlocks in cleanupGlobalSets() as it's called for each ----
2756 // iteration. ----
2757 DeadBlocks.clear(); 0
2758 ----
2759 if (MSSA && VerifyMemorySSA) 0
2760 MSSA->verifyMemorySSA(); 0
2761 ----
2762 return Changed; 0
2763 } 0
2764 ----
2765 bool GVNPass::processBlock(BasicBlock *BB) { 0
2766 // FIXME: Kill off InstrsToErase by doing erasing eagerly in a helper function ----
2767 // (and incrementing BI before processing an instruction). ----
2768 assert(InstrsToErase.empty() && 0
2769 "We expect InstrsToErase to be empty across iterations"); ----
2770 if (DeadBlocks.count(BB)) 0
2771 return false; 0
2772 ----
2773 // Clearing map before every BB because it can be used only for single BB. ----
2774 ReplaceOperandsWithMap.clear(); 0
2775 bool ChangedFunction = false; 0
2776 ----
2777 // Since we may not have visited the input blocks of the phis, we can't ----
2778 // use our normal hash approach for phis. Instead, simply look for ----
2779 // obvious duplicates. The first pass of GVN will tend to create ----
2780 // identical phis, and the second or later passes can eliminate them. ----
2781 ChangedFunction |= EliminateDuplicatePHINodes(BB); 0
2782 ----
2783 for (BasicBlock::iterator BI = BB->begin(), BE = BB->end(); 0
2784 BI != BE;) { 0
2785 if (!ReplaceOperandsWithMap.empty()) 0
2786 ChangedFunction |= replaceOperandsForInBlockEquality(&*BI); 0
2787 ChangedFunction |= processInstruction(&*BI); 0
2788 ----
2789 if (InstrsToErase.empty()) { 0
2790 ++BI; 0
2791 continue; 0
2792 } ----
2793 ----
2794 // If we need some instructions deleted, do it now. ----
2795 NumGVNInstr += InstrsToErase.size(); 0
2796 ----
2797 // Avoid iterator invalidation. ----
2798 bool AtStart = BI == BB->begin(); 0
2799 if (!AtStart) 0
2800 --BI; 0
2801 ----
2802 for (auto *I : InstrsToErase) { 0
2803 assert(I->getParent() == BB && "Removing instruction from wrong block?"); 0
2804 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "GVN removed: " << *I << '\n'); 0
2805 salvageKnowledge(I, AC); 0
2806 salvageDebugInfo(*I); 0
2807 removeInstruction(I); 0
2808 } ----
2809 InstrsToErase.clear(); 0
2810 ----
2811 if (AtStart) 0
2812 BI = BB->begin(); 0
2813 else ----
2814 ++BI; 0
2815 } ----
2816 ----
2817 return ChangedFunction; 0
2818 } ----
2819 ----
2820 // Instantiate an expression in a predecessor that lacked it. ----
2821 bool GVNPass::performScalarPREInsertion(Instruction *Instr, BasicBlock *Pred, 0
2822 BasicBlock *Curr, unsigned int ValNo) { ----
2823 // Because we are going top-down through the block, all value numbers ----
2824 // will be available in the predecessor by the time we need them. Any ----
2825 // that weren't originally present will have been instantiated earlier ----
2826 // in this loop. ----
2827 bool success = true; 0
2828 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Instr->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
2829 Value *Op = Instr->getOperand(i); 0
2830 if (isa(Op) || isa(Op) || isa(Op)) 0
2831 continue; 0
2832 // This could be a newly inserted instruction, in which case, we won't ----
2833 // find a value number, and should give up before we hurt ourselves. ----
2834 // FIXME: Rewrite the infrastructure to let it easier to value number ----
2835 // and process newly inserted instructions. ----
2836 if (!VN.exists(Op)) { 0
2837 success = false; 0
2838 break; 0
2839 } ----
2840 uint32_t TValNo = ----
2841 VN.phiTranslate(Pred, Curr, VN.lookup(Op), *this); 0
2842 if (Value *V = findLeader(Pred, TValNo)) { 0
2843 Instr->setOperand(i, V); 0
2844 } else { ----
2845 success = false; 0
2846 break; 0
2847 } ----
2848 } ----
2849 ----
2850 // Fail out if we encounter an operand that is not available in ----
2851 // the PRE predecessor. This is typically because of loads which ----
2852 // are not value numbered precisely. ----
2853 if (!success) 0
2854 return false; 0
2855 ----
2856 Instr->insertBefore(Pred->getTerminator()); 0
2857 Instr->setName(Instr->getName() + ".pre"); 0
2858 Instr->setDebugLoc(Instr->getDebugLoc()); 0
2859 ----
2860 ICF->insertInstructionTo(Instr, Pred); 0
2861 ----
2862 unsigned Num = VN.lookupOrAdd(Instr); 0
2863 VN.add(Instr, Num); 0
2864 ----
2865 // Update the availability map to include the new instruction. ----
2866 addToLeaderTable(Num, Instr, Pred); 0
2867 return true; 0
2868 } ----
2869 ----
2870 bool GVNPass::performScalarPRE(Instruction *CurInst) { 0
2871 if (isa(CurInst) || CurInst->isTerminator() || 0
2872 isa(CurInst) || CurInst->getType()->isVoidTy() || 0
2873 CurInst->mayReadFromMemory() || CurInst->mayHaveSideEffects() || 0
2874 isa(CurInst)) 0
2875 return false; 0
2876 ----
2877 // Don't do PRE on compares. The PHI would prevent CodeGenPrepare from ----
2878 // sinking the compare again, and it would force the code generator to ----
2879 // move the i1 from processor flags or predicate registers into a general ----
2880 // purpose register. ----
2881 if (isa(CurInst)) 0
2882 return false; 0
2883 ----
2884 // Don't do PRE on GEPs. The inserted PHI would prevent CodeGenPrepare from ----
2885 // sinking the addressing mode computation back to its uses. Extending the ----
2886 // GEP's live range increases the register pressure, and therefore it can ----
2887 // introduce unnecessary spills. ----
2888 // ----
2889 // This doesn't prevent Load PRE. PHI translation will make the GEP available ----
2890 // to the load by moving it to the predecessor block if necessary. ----
2891 if (isa(CurInst)) 0
2892 return false; 0
2893 ----
2894 if (auto *CallB = dyn_cast(CurInst)) { 0
2895 // We don't currently value number ANY inline asm calls. ----
2896 if (CallB->isInlineAsm()) 0
2897 return false; 0
2898 } ----
2899 ----
2900 uint32_t ValNo = VN.lookup(CurInst); 0
2901 ----
2902 // Look for the predecessors for PRE opportunities. We're ----
2903 // only trying to solve the basic diamond case, where ----
2904 // a value is computed in the successor and one predecessor, ----
2905 // but not the other. We also explicitly disallow cases ----
2906 // where the successor is its own predecessor, because they're ----
2907 // more complicated to get right. ----
2908 unsigned NumWith = 0; 0

2977 if (isCriticalEdge(PREPred->getTerminator(), SuccNum)) { 0

2980 } ----

2983 if (!performScalarPREInsertion(PREInstr, PREPred, CurrentBlock, ValNo)) { 0

2986 verifyRemoved(PREInstr); 0

2991 } ----
2992 ----

2994 // not have needed insertions. ----
2995 assert(PREInstr != nullptr || NumWithout == 0); 0

2998 ----

3032 /// Perform a purely local form of PRE that looks for diamond ----
3033 /// control flow patterns and attempts to perform simple PRE at the join point. ----
3034 bool GVNPass::performPRE(Function &F) { 0
3035 bool Changed = false; 0

3037 // Nothing to PRE in the entry block. ----

3039 continue; 0
3040 ----

3042 if (CurrentBlock->isEHPad()) 0
3043 continue; 0
3044 ----

3046 BE = CurrentBlock->end(); 0
3047 BI != BE;) { 0
3048 Instruction *CurInst = &*BI++; 0
3049 Changed |= performScalarPRE(CurInst); 0
3050 } ----
3051 } 0
3052 ----
3053 if (splitCriticalEdges()) 0
3054 Changed = true; 0
3055 ----
3056 return Changed; 0
3057 } ----

3075 /// Split critical edges found during the previous ----

3133 /// Verify that the specified instruction does not occur in our ----
3134 /// internal data structures. ----
3135 void GVNPass::verifyRemoved(const Instruction *Inst) const { 0
3136 VN.verifyRemoved(Inst); 0
3137 ----
3138 // Walk through the value number scope to make sure the instruction isn't ----
3139 // ferreted away in it. ----
3140 for (const auto &I : LeaderTable) { 0

3142 assert(Node->Val != Inst && "Inst still in value numbering scope!"); 0

3151 /// BB is declared dead, which implied other blocks become dead as well. This ----
3152 /// function is to add all these blocks to "DeadBlocks". For the dead blocks' ----
3153 /// live successors, update their phi nodes by replacing the operands ----
3154 /// corresponding to dead blocks with UndefVal. ----
3155 void GVNPass::addDeadBlock(BasicBlock *BB) { 0
3156 SmallVector NewDead; 0
3157 SmallSetVector DF; 0
3158 ----
3159 NewDead.push_back(BB); 0
3160 while (!NewDead.empty()) { 0
3161 BasicBlock *D = NewDead.pop_back_val(); 0
3162 if (DeadBlocks.count(D)) 0
3163 continue; 0
3164 ----
3165 // All blocks dominated by D are dead. ----
3166 SmallVector Dom; 0
3167 DT->getDescendants(D, Dom); 0
3168 DeadBlocks.insert(Dom.begin(), Dom.end()); 0
3169 ----
3170 // Figure out the dominance-frontier(D). ----
3171 for (BasicBlock *B : Dom) { 0
3172 for (BasicBlock *S : successors(B)) { 0
3173 if (DeadBlocks.count(S)) 0
3174 continue; 0
3175 ----

3177 for (BasicBlock *P : predecessors(S)) 0
3178 if (!DeadBlocks.count(P)) { 0
3179 AllPredDead = false; 0
3180 break; 0
3181 } ----
3182 ----
3183 if (!AllPredDead) { 0
3184 // S could be proved dead later on. That is why we don't update phi ----
3185 // operands at this moment. ----
3186 DF.insert(S); 0
3187 } else { ----
3188 // While S is not dominated by D, it is dead by now. This could take ----
3189 // place if S already have a dead predecessor before D is declared ----
3190 // dead. ----
3191 NewDead.push_back(S); 0
3192 } ----
3193 } ----
3194 } ----
3195 } 0
3196 ----
3197 // For the dead blocks' live successors, update their phi nodes by replacing ----
3198 // the operands corresponding to dead blocks with UndefVal. ----
3199 for (BasicBlock *B : DF) { 0
3200 if (DeadBlocks.count(B)) 0
3201 continue; 0
3202 ----
3203 // First, split the critical edges. This might also create additional blocks ----
3204 // to preserve LoopSimplify form and adjust edges accordingly. ----
3205 SmallVector Preds(predecessors(B)); 0
3206 for (BasicBlock *P : Preds) { 0
3207 if (!DeadBlocks.count(P)) 0
3208 continue; 0

3211 isCriticalEdge(P->getTerminator(), B)) { 0

3219 if (!DeadBlocks.count(P)) 0
3220 continue; 0

3223 if (MD) 0
3224 MD->invalidateCachedPointerInfo(&Phi); 0
3225 } ----
3226 } ----
3227 } 0
3228 } 0
3229 ----
3230 // If the given branch is recognized as a foldable branch (i.e. conditional ----
3231 // branch with constant condition), it will perform following analyses and ----
3232 // transformation. ----
3233 // 1) If the dead out-coming edge is a critical-edge, split it. Let ----
3234 // R be the target of the dead out-coming edge. ----
3235 // 1) Identify the set of dead blocks implied by the branch's dead outcoming ----
3236 // edge. The result of this step will be {X| X is dominated by R} ----
3237 // 2) Identify those blocks which haves at least one dead predecessor. The ----
3238 // result of this step will be dominance-frontier(R). ----
3239 // 3) Update the PHIs in DF(R) by replacing the operands corresponding to ----
3240 // dead blocks with "UndefVal" in an hope these PHIs will optimized away. ----
3241 // ----
3242 // Return true iff *NEW* dead code are found. ----
3243 bool GVNPass::processFoldableCondBr(BranchInst *BI) { 0
3244 if (!BI || BI->isUnconditional()) 0
3245 return false; 0
3246 ----
3247 // If a branch has two identical successors, we cannot declare either dead. ----
3248 if (BI->getSuccessor(0) == BI->getSuccessor(1)) 0
3249 return false; 0
3250 ----
3251 ConstantInt *Cond = dyn_cast(BI->getCondition()); 0
3252 if (!Cond) 0
3253 return false; 0
3254 ----
3255 BasicBlock *DeadRoot = ----
3256 Cond->getZExtValue() ? BI->getSuccessor(1) : BI->getSuccessor(0); 0
3257 if (DeadBlocks.count(DeadRoot)) 0
3258 return false; 0
3259 ----
3260 if (!DeadRoot->getSinglePredecessor()) 0
3261 DeadRoot = splitCriticalEdges(BI->getParent(), DeadRoot); 0
3262 ----
3263 addDeadBlock(DeadRoot); 0
3264 return true; 0
3265 } ----
3266 ----
3267 // performPRE() will trigger assert if it comes across an instruction without ----
3268 // associated val-num. As it normally has far more live instructions than dead ----
3269 // instructions, it makes more sense just to "fabricate" a val-number for the ----
3270 // dead code than checking if instruction involved is dead or not. ----
3271 void GVNPass::assignValNumForDeadCode() { 0
3272 for (BasicBlock *BB : DeadBlocks) { 0
3273 for (Instruction &Inst : *BB) { 0

3275 addToLeaderTable(ValNum, &Inst, BB); 0
3276 } ----
3277 } ----
3278 } 0
